INSERT INTO `tour_program` VALUES (1,1,1,'Eiffel Tower & Seine Cruise','Begin your Parisian adventure with a visit to the iconic Eiffel Tower, where you can ascend to the summit for breathtaking city views. Stroll along the Champ de Mars, soaking in the vibrant atmosphere and capturing photos of this global landmark. Conclude the day with a romantic Seine River cruise, gliding past illuminated monuments like Notre-Dame and the Louvre as the city sparkles at dusk.'),(2,1,2,'Louvre Museum & Tuileries','Immerse yourself in art at the Louvre Museum, where you’ll marvel at masterpieces like the Mona Lisa and Venus de Milo amidst grand galleries. Wander through the adjacent Tuileries Garden, admiring manicured lawns, sculptures, and serene fountains. Enjoy a leisurely café lunch nearby, soaking in the Parisian ambiance as street performers entertain.'),(3,1,3,'Montmartre & Sacré-Cœur','Explore the bohemian Montmartre district, wandering cobblestone streets lined with charming cafés and artist studios once frequented by Picasso and Van Gogh. Visit the stunning Sacré-Cœur Basilica atop the hill, offering panoramic views of Paris from its dome. Savor a traditional French dinner at a local bistro, surrounded by the neighborhood’s lively, artistic vibe.'),(4,2,1,'Versailles Palace','Step into royal grandeur at the Palace of Versailles, touring the opulent Hall of Mirrors and the king’s lavish apartments. Stroll through the sprawling gardens, adorned with fountains, sculptures, and manicured hedges, and opt for a bike ride to explore further. Enjoy a picnic by the Grand Canal, soaking in the serene beauty of this UNESCO World Heritage site.'),(5,2,2,'Louvre & Orsay Museums','Discover the Louvre’s vast collection, from ancient Egyptian artifacts to Renaissance masterpieces, with a guided tour highlighting key works. Cross the Seine to the Musée d’Orsay, where Impressionist paintings by Monet and Van Gogh dazzle in a converted train station. End the day with a coffee at a nearby café, reflecting on the artistic treasures you’ve seen.'),(6,2,3,'Notre-Dame & Latin Quarter','Admire the Gothic splendor of Notre-Dame Cathedral, exploring its intricate facade and climbing the towers for city views. Wander the lively Latin Quarter, with its narrow streets filled with bookstores, bistros, and historic churches like Saint-Séverin. Enjoy a crepe from a street vendor while soaking in the intellectual and bohemian atmosphere.'),(7,2,4,'Montmartre & Moulin Rouge','Roam Montmartre’s artistic enclave, visiting Place du Tertre where local artists paint and sell their work. Tour the Sacré-Cœur Basilica, marveling at its Romano-Byzantine architecture and sweeping Parisian vistas. Cap the evening with a dazzling cabaret performance at the iconic Moulin Rouge, complete with can-can dancers and champagne.'),(8,2,5,'Seine Cruise & Eiffel Tower','Embark on a daytime Seine River cruise, passing landmarks like the Grand Palais and Île de la Cité while learning about Paris’s history. Ascend the Eiffel Tower for a sunset view, capturing photos from its observation decks. Dine at a nearby brasserie, savoring classic French dishes like coq au vin in the tower’s glowing ambiance.'),(9,2,6,'Wine Tasting Experience','Join a guided wine tasting in a historic Parisian cellar, sampling regional varietals from Bordeaux to Champagne with expert insights. Learn about France’s winemaking heritage while pairing wines with artisanal cheeses and charcuterie. Relax in the cozy, candlelit setting, sharing stories with fellow travelers.'),(10,2,7,'Day Trip to Giverny','Journey to Giverny to explore Claude Monet’s home and gardens, where vibrant flowerbeds and the famous water lily pond inspire awe. Stroll the charming village, visiting local art galleries and quaint cafés. Return to Paris with a deeper appreciation for Impressionism, perhaps sketching your own inspired scene.'),(11,3,1,'Promenade des Anglais','Stroll along the iconic Promenade des Anglais, where palm trees frame sparkling Mediterranean views and vibrant beach life unfolds. Relax on the pebbled shores or rent a lounge chair to soak up the Riviera sun. Enjoy a gelato from a seaside vendor while watching joggers and cyclists pass by.'),(12,3,2,'Old Town & Castle Hill','Wander Nice’s colorful Old Town, exploring narrow alleys filled with Baroque churches, bustling markets, and pastel-hued buildings. Climb to Castle Hill for panoramic views of the Baie des Anges and the city’s red-tiled rooftops. Savor a lunch of socca and salade niçoise at a charming café in Place Rossetti.'),(13,3,3,'Matisse Museum','Visit the Matisse Museum in Cimiez, showcasing the artist’s vibrant paintings, sculptures, and paper cutouts in a 17th-century villa. Explore the nearby Roman ruins and Franciscan monastery, steeped in history and surrounded by olive groves. Relax in the serene Cimiez Gardens, perfect for a leisurely picnic.'),(14,3,4,'Market Tour & Cooking Class','Shop for fresh produce and local specialties at Cours Saleya’s vibrant market, guided by a local chef. Participate in a hands-on Niçoise cooking class, learning to prepare dishes like ratatouille or pissaladière. Enjoy your culinary creations over lunch, paired with a glass of Provençal rosé.'),(15,4,1,'Nice Old Town','Dive into Nice’s Old Town, where flower markets, gelaterias, and historic sites like the Palais Lascaris create a lively atmosphere. Savor a coffee in Place Rossetti, watching street performers and locals mingle. Climb Castle Hill at dusk for stunning views of the coastline and city lights.'),(16,4,2,'Monaco & Monte Carlo','Travel to Monaco, touring the Prince’s Palace and watching the ceremonial guard change. Visit the glamorous Monte Carlo Casino, admiring its Belle Époque architecture and lush gardens. Stroll the Larvotto Beach promenade, enjoying Mediterranean views and upscale boutiques.'),(17,4,3,'Cannes & Antibes','Walk Cannes’ La Croisette, passing luxury hotels and the Palais des Festivals, home of the film festival. Explore Antibes’ fortified old town, with its charming streets and the Picasso Museum housed in the Château Grimaldi. Relax on Antibes’ sandy beaches, dipping into the clear waters.'),(18,4,4,'Eze & Villefranche','Discover Eze, a medieval hilltop village with stone streets, artisan shops, and exotic gardens overlooking the sea. Visit Villefranche-sur-Mer’s colorful waterfront, lined with pastel villas and seafood restaurants. Swim in the calm bay or explore the 16th-century Citadel for historic charm.'),(19,4,5,'Matisse & Chagall Museums','Tour the Matisse Museum, admiring the artist’s bold works in the serene Cimiez neighborhood. Visit the Chagall Museum, where vibrant biblical paintings and stained-glass windows captivate. Enjoy a leisurely lunch in a nearby garden café, surrounded by olive trees and sculptures.'),(20,4,6,'Grasse Perfume Tour','Journey to Grasse, the perfume capital, touring the Fragonard factory to learn about fragrance creation. Stroll the town’s historic center, with its fountain-filled squares and Provençal charm. Create your own signature scent in a perfume-making workshop, a unique Riviera keepsake.'),(21,5,1,'Prado Museum','Immerse yourself in the Prado Museum, admiring masterpieces by Goya, Velázquez, and El Greco in grand galleries. Join a guided tour to uncover the stories behind iconic works like Las Meninas. Relax with a coffee at the museum café, surrounded by lush gardens.'),(22,5,2,'Royal Palace & Plaza Mayor','Tour the opulent Royal Palace, exploring its lavish rooms, throne hall, and armory filled with historic treasures. Wander to Plaza Mayor, a vibrant square framed by red arcades, perfect for people-watching. Savor churros con chocolate at a nearby café, soaking in Madrid’s lively ambiance.'),(23,5,3,'Retiro Park & Tapas','Stroll through Retiro Park, rowing a boat on the lake or admiring the Crystal Palace’s glass architecture. Explore the park’s rose garden and shaded pathways, ideal for a relaxing morning. End the day with a guided tapas tour, sampling jamón ibérico and patatas bravas at local taverns.'),(24,6,1,'Prado & Reina Sofía','Explore the Prado Museum’s vast collection of European art, from Titian to Bosch, with a focus on Spanish masters. Visit the Reina Sofía to see Picasso’s Guernica and modern works by Dalí and Miró. Enjoy a light lunch at a nearby tapas bar, discussing the day’s artistic highlights.'),(25,6,2,'Royal Palace & Almudena','Step inside the Royal Palace, marveling at its frescoed ceilings, chandeliers, and royal collections. Visit the adjacent Almudena Cathedral, with its colorful dome and neo-Gothic interior. Stroll through the Sabatini Gardens, capturing photos of the palace’s elegant facade.'),(26,6,3,'Toledo Day Trip','Journey to Toledo, exploring its medieval streets, Gothic cathedral, and El Greco’s masterpieces. Visit the Alcázar and Synagogue of Santa María la Blanca, reflecting the city’s multicultural heritage. Savor a traditional lunch of manchego cheese and local wines in a historic tavern.'),(27,6,4,'Segovia & Avila','Discover Segovia’s Roman aqueduct and fairy-tale Alcázar, said to inspire Disney’s Cinderella Castle. Tour Avila’s perfectly preserved medieval walls and Romanesque churches. Enjoy a hearty Castilian lunch, featuring cochinillo (roast suckling pig), in Segovia’s charming old town.'),(28,6,5,'Retiro & Botanical Garden','Relax in Retiro Park, wandering through its fountains, sculptures, and serene boating lake. Visit the Royal Botanical Garden, showcasing exotic plants and tranquil pathways. Unwind with a picnic under the park’s ancient trees, enjoying Madrid’s sunny weather.'),(29,6,6,'Flamenco Show','Experience an authentic flamenco performance at a historic tablao, with passionate dancers and soulful guitarists. Learn about flamenco’s cultural roots during a pre-show talk. Savor a glass of sangria while immersed in the electrifying atmosphere of this Spanish tradition.'),(30,6,7,'Tapas & Wine Tour','Embark on a guided tapas tour through Madrid’s vibrant neighborhoods, tasting croquetas, gambas al ajillo, and regional wines. Visit historic taverns and modern gastrobars, learning about Spanish culinary traditions. End the evening in a lively plaza, mingling with locals over shared plates.'),(31,6,8,'El Escorial Monastery','Tour the El Escorial Monastery, a UNESCO site with its grand basilica, royal crypt, and Renaissance library. Explore the surrounding gardens and enjoy views of the Sierra de Guadarrama. Reflect on Spain’s imperial past over a leisurely lunch in the nearby town.'),(32,7,1,'Sagrada Familia','Marvel at Gaudí’s Sagrada Familia, exploring its towering facades and vibrant stained-glass interiors on a guided tour. Learn about the basilica’s ongoing construction and symbolic design, a masterpiece of modernist architecture. Capture photos from the nearby plaza, framed by the spires’ intricate details.'),(33,7,2,'Park Güell & Casa Batlló','Wander Park Güell’s colorful mosaics, whimsical structures, and panoramic city views, designed by Gaudí. Visit Casa Batlló, with its dragon-inspired roof and flowing, organic interiors. Enjoy a coffee at a nearby café, admiring the Eixample district’s modernist architecture.'),(34,7,3,'Gothic Quarter','Explore the Gothic Quarter’s narrow medieval streets, discovering hidden squares and the Gothic Barcelona Cathedral. Visit the ancient Roman walls and the bustling Plaça Reial, lined with palm trees and tapas bars. Savor a lunch of paella in a historic restaurant, soaking in the neighborhood’s charm.'),(35,7,4,'La Rambla & Boqueria','Stroll La Rambla, Barcelona’s lively boulevard, passing street performers, flower stalls, and iconic landmarks like the Liceu Theatre. Shop for fresh produce and local delicacies at La Boqueria Market, a feast for the senses. End the day with a glass of cava at a nearby bar, reflecting on your Catalan adventure.'),(36,8,1,'Sagrada Familia & Hospital Sant Pau','Tour Gaudí’s Sagrada Familia, marveling at its intricate Nativity Facade and towering columns inspired by nature. Visit the Hospital Sant Pau, a modernist gem with colorful tiles and lush courtyards. Enjoy a leisurely lunch nearby, surrounded by Barcelona’s architectural wonders.'),(37,8,2,'Park Güell & Casa Milà','Explore Park Güell’s vibrant mosaics and surreal structures, offering stunning views of Barcelona. Tour Casa Milà (La Pedrera), with its undulating stone facade and rooftop chimneys resembling warriors. Relax with a gelato in the chic Passeig de Gràcia, admiring nearby modernist buildings.'),(38,8,3,'Montserrat Day Trip','Journey to Montserrat, a jagged mountain range, and tour its Benedictine monastery, home to the Black Madonna statue. Hike scenic trails or ride the funicular for breathtaking views of the Catalan countryside. Enjoy a local lunch featuring crema catalana, savoring the serene atmosphere.'),(39,8,4,'Costa Brava Beaches','Relax on the Costa Brava’s pristine beaches, with crystal waters and charming coves like Tamariu or Llafranc. Explore the medieval village of Pals, with its stone arches and cobblestone streets. Savor fresh seafood at a seaside restaurant, basking in the Mediterranean sun.'),(40,8,5,'Dalí Museum in Figueres','Visit the Dalí Theatre-Museum in Figueres, a surreal wonderland of Salvador Dalí’s eccentric artworks and installations. Explore the nearby Dalí Jewels exhibit, showcasing his intricate designs. Enjoy a tapas lunch in Figueres’ vibrant town center, reflecting on Dalí’s genius.'),(41,8,6,'Gothic Quarter & Picasso','Wander the Gothic Quarter, visiting the Picasso Museum to see early works by the legendary artist. Discover hidden gems like the Santa Maria del Mar church and lively Plaça del Rei. Dine at a traditional Catalan restaurant, sampling calcots and romesco sauce.'),(42,8,7,'Tapas & Flamenco','Embark on a tapas crawl through El Born, tasting fideuà and bombas paired with local wines. Enjoy a passionate flamenco performance at a historic venue, with rhythmic guitar and soulful singing. End the night in a lively plaza, mingling with locals over sangria.'),(43,9,1,'Colosseum & Roman Forum','Step into history at the Colosseum, exploring the ancient arena where gladiators once fought, with a guided tour. Wander the Roman Forum, marveling at ruins like the Temple of Saturn and Arch of Titus. Enjoy a gelato near the Palatine Hill, soaking in Rome’s ancient grandeur.'),(44,9,2,'Pantheon & Piazza Navona','Visit the Pantheon, admiring its massive dome and ancient oculus, a marvel of Roman engineering. Stroll to Piazza Navona, with its ornate fountains and lively street artists. Savor a Roman pizza lunch at a nearby trattoria, watching the bustling square come alive.'),(45,9,3,'Trevi Fountain & Spanish Steps','Toss a coin into the Trevi Fountain, marveling at its Baroque sculptures and wishing for a return to Rome. Climb the Spanish Steps, enjoying views of the Piazza di Spagna and luxury boutiques. End the day with a cappuccino at a historic café, reflecting on Rome’s timeless charm.'),(46,10,1,'Colosseum & Palatine Hill','Tour the Colosseum, imagining gladiatorial battles while exploring its underground chambers. Climb Palatine Hill to see imperial palaces and sweeping views of the Roman Forum. Enjoy a picnic lunch amidst the ruins, surrounded by ancient pines and history.'),(47,10,2,'Vatican Museums & St. Peter’s','Explore the Vatican Museums, marveling at the Sistine Chapel’s Michelangelo frescoes and the Raphael Rooms. Visit St. Peter’s Basilica, climbing its dome for panoramic views of Vatican City. Savor a coffee in Piazza San Pietro, watching pilgrims and tourists gather.'),(48,10,3,'Pantheon & Campo de’ Fiori','Admire the Pantheon’s ancient architecture, stepping inside to see its perfectly preserved interior. Wander to Campo de’ Fiori, browsing its vibrant market for fresh produce and souvenirs. Enjoy a lunch of carbonara at a local osteria, soaking in the lively neighborhood atmosphere.'),(49,10,4,'Appian Way & Catacombs','Cycle along the ancient Appian Way, passing historic villas, aqueducts, and lush countryside. Explore the Catacombs of San Callisto, descending into underground tunnels filled with early Christian art. Relax with a rustic lunch at a nearby trattoria, enjoying views of the Roman landscape.'),(50,10,5,'Trastevere & Cooking Class','Stroll Trastevere’s charming streets, lined with ivy-covered buildings, artisan shops, and the Santa Maria in Trastevere church. Join a hands-on pasta-making class, learning to craft fettuccine and tiramisu with a local chef. Feast on your creations, paired with Chianti, in a cozy Roman kitchen.'),(51,10,6,'Borghese Gallery','Tour the Borghese Gallery, admiring Bernini’s dynamic sculptures and Caravaggio’s dramatic paintings in a lush villa. Stroll the surrounding Villa Borghese gardens, renting a bike or rowing on the lake. Enjoy an aperitivo at a garden café, savoring the serene ambiance.'),(52,10,7,'Ostia Antica Day Trip','Explore Ostia Antica, Rome’s ancient port, wandering well-preserved ruins like the amphitheater and mosaiced baths. Learn about daily life in Roman times with a guided tour of the site’s insulae and taverns. Savor a seafood lunch near the Tiber River, reflecting on Rome’s vast history.'),(53,11,1,'Duomo & Rooftop','Marvel at Milan’s Gothic Duomo, exploring its intricate spires and stained-glass windows on a guided tour. Ascend to the rooftop terraces for panoramic views of the city and distant Alps. Enjoy a coffee in Piazza del Duomo, watching the bustling heart of Milan.'),(54,11,2,'Last Supper & Sforza Castle','Admire Leonardo da Vinci’s Last Supper, a Renaissance masterpiece, in the Santa Maria delle Grazie convent. Tour Sforza Castle’s museums, showcasing Michelangelo’s Pietà Rondanini and historic artifacts. Stroll the castle’s courtyards, soaking in Milan’s medieval heritage.'),(55,11,3,'Galleria & Fashion District','Shop in the elegant Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, a glass-vaulted arcade filled with luxury boutiques and historic cafés. Explore the Quadrilatero della Moda, browsing flagship stores from Gucci to Prada. Savor a risotto alla Milanese lunch at a chic restaurant, embracing Milan’s stylish vibe.'),(56,12,1,'Duomo & La Scala','Tour Milan’s Duomo, climbing to its rooftop for stunning city views and intricate Gothic details. Visit La Scala, exploring its opulent theater and museum dedicated to opera legends like Verdi. Enjoy an aperitivo in Piazza della Scala, surrounded by Milan’s cultural heart.'),(57,12,2,'Last Supper & Brera','See da Vinci’s Last Supper, marveling at its emotional depth in a quiet convent setting. Wander the Brera district, visiting the Pinacoteca di Brera for Renaissance masterpieces by Raphael and Caravaggio. Dine at a cozy trattoria, savoring ossobuco in Brera’s artistic ambiance.'),(58,12,3,'Lake Como Day Trip','Cruise Lake Como, visiting Bellagio’s charming streets and Villa del Balbianello’s lush gardens. Admire the lake’s serene waters and snow-capped Alps from a scenic boat ride. Savor a lakeside lunch of fresh fish, soaking in the tranquil beauty of this Italian gem.'),(59,12,4,'Bergamo’s Citta Alta','Explore Bergamo’s Citta Alta, a medieval hilltop town with cobblestone streets and the grand Basilica of Santa Maria Maggiore. Stroll the Venetian walls for panoramic views of the Lombard plains. Enjoy a polenta lunch at a historic osteria, embracing Bergamo’s rustic charm.'),(60,12,5,'Fashion & Design Tour','Tour Milan’s fashion district, visiting the Armani/Silos museum to explore Italian design evolution. Shop in the Quadrilatero, browsing high-end boutiques and emerging designer stores. End with a cocktail at a rooftop bar, overlooking Milan’s glittering skyline.'),(61,12,6,'Navigli Canal Cruise','Cruise Milan’s Navigli canals, passing historic bridges and vibrant waterfront cafés. Explore the Navigli district’s art galleries, antique shops, and lively aperitivo scene. Dine on Lombard specialties like cotoletta alla Milanese, enjoying the bohemian atmosphere.'),(62,13,1,'St. Mark’s & Doge’s Palace','Visit St. Mark’s Basilica, marveling at its golden mosaics and Byzantine domes in Venice’s heart. Tour the Doge’s Palace, exploring its ornate council chambers and the haunting Bridge of Sighs. Enjoy a cappuccino in Piazza San Marco, watching pigeons and tourists fill the square.'),(63,13,2,'Gondola Ride & Rialto','Glide through Venice’s canals on a private gondola ride, passing historic palazzos and hidden waterways. Explore the bustling Rialto Bridge and its lively market, sampling cicchetti (Venetian tapas). Savor a seafood lunch at a canal-side trattoria, soaking in the city’s aquatic charm.'),(64,13,3,'Accademia Gallery','Tour the Accademia Gallery, admiring Venetian masterpieces by Titian, Tintoretto, and Veronese. Wander the Dorsoduro district, discovering quiet squares and artisan workshops. End with a spritz at a local bacaro, embracing Venice’s laid-back evening vibe.'),(65,14,1,'St. Mark’s & Campanile','Explore St. Mark’s Basilica, with its shimmering mosaics and Pala d’Oro altarpiece, a Byzantine treasure. Climb the Campanile for panoramic views of Venice’s lagoon and red-tiled rooftops. Relax with a gelato in Piazza San Marco, soaking in the square’s lively energy.'),(66,14,2,'Doge’s Palace & Bridge of Sighs','Tour the Doge’s Palace, marveling at its grand staircases, gilded rooms, and Tintoretto’s massive Paradise painting. Cross the Bridge of Sighs, imagining the prisoners’ final views of Venice. Enjoy a seafood dinner by the Grand Canal, watching gondolas glide past.'),(67,14,3,'Murano Glass Tour','Visit Murano, watching master glassblowers craft intricate sculptures and chandeliers in historic furnaces. Explore the island’s Glass Museum and quaint canals lined with colorful houses. Purchase a unique glass souvenir and enjoy a light lunch at a local trattoria.'),(68,14,4,'Burano & Torcello','Discover Burano’s vibrant, multicolored houses and browse its famous lace-making shops. Visit Torcello, exploring the ancient Cathedral of Santa Maria Assunta and its stunning mosaics. Savor a risotto lunch on Burano, enjoying views of the serene lagoon.'),(69,14,5,'Grand Canal Cruise','Cruise the Grand Canal by vaporetto, passing grand palazzos like Ca’ d’Oro and the Rialto Bridge. Learn about Venice’s mercantile history from a guide, spotting hidden architectural gems. Stop for an aperitivo at a canal-side bar, watching the city’s aquatic life unfold.'),(70,14,6,'Peggy Guggenheim Collection','Tour the Peggy Guggenheim Collection, showcasing modern art by Picasso, Pollock, and Magritte in a serene palazzo. Stroll the Dorsoduro’s quiet canals, visiting local galleries and churches like Santa Maria della Salute. End with a prosecco toast at a rooftop terrace, overlooking Venice’s skyline.'),(71,15,1,'Tower of London','Explore the Tower of London, discovering the Crown Jewels’ dazzling display and tales of royal intrigue. Tour the White Tower and medieval armory, guided by a Yeoman Warder (Beefeater). Enjoy a pub lunch nearby, savoring fish and chips by the Thames.'),(72,15,2,'Buckingham Palace & Westminster','Witness the Changing of the Guard at Buckingham Palace, soaking in the pomp and pageantry. Visit Westminster Abbey, marveling at its Gothic arches and the Coronation Chair. Stroll Parliament Square, capturing photos of Big Ben and the Houses of Parliament.'),(73,15,3,'British Museum','Wander the British Museum, exploring treasures like the Rosetta Stone, Egyptian mummies, and Parthenon sculptures. Join a guided tour to uncover the stories behind these global artifacts. Relax with afternoon tea in the museum’s Great Court, under its iconic glass roof.'),(74,15,4,'Covent Garden & Thames Cruise','Shop and dine in Covent Garden, enjoying street performers and the vibrant Apple Market. Embark on a Thames River cruise, passing landmarks like the Shard and Tower Bridge. End with a pint at a riverside pub, reflecting on London’s dynamic energy.'),(75,16,1,'Tower Bridge & St. Paul’s','Walk across the iconic Tower Bridge, exploring its Victorian engine rooms and glass walkway with river views. Tour St. Paul’s Cathedral, climbing its dome for panoramic city vistas. Enjoy a traditional Sunday roast at a nearby pub, embracing London’s historic charm.'),(76,16,2,'Westminster & Big Ben','Visit Westminster Abbey, admiring its royal tombs and Poet’s Corner, steeped in centuries of history. Stroll to the Houses of Parliament, photographing Big Ben’s iconic clock tower. Relax in St. James’s Park, feeding pelicans and enjoying views of Buckingham Palace.'),(77,16,3,'British Museum & Bloomsbury','Explore the British Museum’s vast collections, from Assyrian reliefs to the Elgin Marbles, with a guided highlights tour. Wander Bloomsbury’s literary streets, passing historic squares and the Charles Dickens Museum. Savor a curry dinner in nearby Fitzrovia, a nod to London’s diverse culinary scene.'),(78,16,4,'Stonehenge & Bath','Journey to Stonehenge, marveling at the ancient stone circle and its mysterious origins. Explore Bath’s Roman Baths and Georgian architecture, including the elegant Royal Crescent. Enjoy a cream tea in Bath, reflecting on England’s rich heritage.'),(79,16,5,'Kensington Museums','Visit the Victoria and Albert Museum, showcasing decorative arts from medieval tapestries to modern fashion. Explore the Natural History Museum’s dinosaur skeletons and dazzling gem collections. Stroll Kensington Gardens, admiring the Albert Memorial and Serpentine Lake.'),(80,16,6,'West End Theatre','Experience a world-class West End show, from musicals like Les Misérables to cutting-edge dramas, in a historic theater. Dine at a pre-theatre restaurant in Soho, sampling modern British cuisine. Wander Leicester Square afterward, soaking in London’s vibrant nightlife.'),(81,16,7,'Greenwich & Cutty Sark','Explore Greenwich, visiting the Royal Observatory and standing on the Prime Meridian line. Tour the Cutty Sark, a 19th-century tea clipper, and learn about its seafaring history. Enjoy a riverside lunch at a Greenwich pub, with views of the Thames and Canary Wharf.'),(82,17,1,'Edinburgh Castle','Tour Edinburgh Castle, exploring the Crown Jewels, Stone of Destiny, and St. Margaret’s Chapel atop Castle Rock. Wander the castle esplanade, enjoying views of the city and distant Firth of Forth. Savor a traditional Scottish lunch, perhaps haggis, at a nearby pub.'),(83,17,2,'Royal Mile & Holyrood','Walk the Royal Mile, passing historic closes, the St. Giles’ Cathedral, and vibrant street performers. Visit the Palace of Holyroodhouse, the King’s official Scottish residence, and its lush gardens. Enjoy a whisky tasting at a local shop, learning about Scotland’s national drink.'),(84,17,3,'Arthur’s Seat Hike','Hike Arthur’s Seat, a dramatic hill in Holyrood Park, for sweeping views of Edinburgh’s skyline and coastline. Explore the park’s lochs and ruins, including St. Anthony’s Chapel. Relax with a picnic at the summit, soaking in the rugged beauty of this ancient volcano.'),(85,18,1,'Edinburgh Castle & Old Town','Discover Edinburgh Castle, with its royal treasures and panoramic views over the city. Wander the Old Town’s medieval streets, exploring hidden wynds and the eerie Mary King’s Close. Dine at a cozy restaurant, sampling Cullen skink and other Scottish dishes.'),(86,18,2,'Royal Mile & Calton Hill','Stroll the Royal Mile, visiting Canongate Kirk and the Scottish Parliament’s modern architecture. Climb Calton Hill for views of Edinburgh’s spires and the iconic monuments like the Nelson Monument. Enjoy a coffee at a nearby café, reflecting on the city’s historic charm.'),(87,18,3,'Loch Ness & Urquhart Castle','Journey to Loch Ness, cruising its mysterious waters in search of the legendary monster. Explore Urquhart Castle’s ruins, with its dramatic lochside setting and turbulent history. Savor a hearty lunch in Drumnadrochit, perhaps trying local venison or salmon.'),(88,18,4,'Glencoe & Fort William','Drive through Glencoe’s breathtaking valley, with rugged peaks and waterfalls, a haven for hikers and photographers. Visit Fort William, exploring its West Highland Museum and Ben Nevis views. Enjoy a traditional pub dinner, warming up with a dram of whisky.'),(89,18,5,'Isle of Skye','Explore the Isle of Skye’s dramatic landscapes, from the Cuillin Mountains to the fairy-tale Dunvegan Castle. Visit the colorful Portree harbor and hike to the Old Man of Storr for stunning vistas. Savor fresh seafood at a local restaurant, embracing Skye’s wild beauty.'),(90,18,6,'Whisky Tasting','Join a guided whisky tasting in Edinburgh, sampling single malts from Speyside to Islay with expert insights. Learn about Scotland’s whisky-making process, from malting to maturation. Relax in a cozy distillery bar, sharing stories with fellow travelers over a final dram.'),(91,18,7,'Stirling Castle','Tour Stirling Castle, a historic stronghold with grand halls and views of the Wallace Monument. Explore the castle’s Renaissance gardens and the Royal Palace’s restored interiors. Enjoy a farewell lunch in Stirling’s old town, savoring Scotland’s rich history.'),(92,19,1,'Schönbrunn Palace','Tour Schönbrunn Palace, exploring its lavish rooms, including the Mirror Hall where Mozart performed. Stroll the palace’s Baroque gardens, with fountains, mazes, and the Gloriette viewpoint. Enjoy a strudel at the palace café, soaking in Vienna’s imperial elegance.'),(93,19,2,'St. Stephen’s & Hofburg','Visit St. Stephen’s Cathedral, climbing its South Tower for panoramic views of Vienna’s rooftops. Explore the Hofburg Palace, with its imperial apartments, Sisi Museum, and silver collection. Savor a Viennese coffee and sachertorte at a historic café nearby.'),(94,19,3,'Opera House Tour','Take a guided tour of the Vienna State Opera, marveling at its neo-Renaissance architecture and gilded auditorium. Learn about its storied history and legendary performances by composers like Strauss. Stroll the Ringstrasse afterward, admiring Vienna’s grand boulevards and landmarks.'),(95,20,1,'Schönbrunn & Belvedere','Explore Schönbrunn Palace’s opulent interiors and sprawling gardens, a UNESCO World Heritage site. Visit Belvedere Palace, admiring Klimt’s The Kiss and its Baroque architecture. Enjoy a light lunch in Belvedere’s gardens, surrounded by fountains and sculptures.'),(96,20,2,'Hofburg & Museumsquartier','Tour the Hofburg Palace, discovering the Imperial Treasury’s crown jewels and Empress Sisi’s apartments. Wander the Museumsquartier, visiting the Leopold Museum for Austrian art by Schiele and Klimt. Relax with a spritzer at a trendy MQ café, soaking in Vienna’s creative vibe.'),(97,20,3,'Melk Abbey Day Trip','Visit Melk Abbey, a Benedictine masterpiece perched above the Danube, with its golden library and frescoed church. Explore the abbey’s gardens and museum, showcasing medieval manuscripts. Savor a regional lunch in Melk’s charming town, enjoying views of the river.'),(98,20,4,'Wachau Valley Cruise','Cruise the Wachau Valley, passing vine-covered hills, medieval castles, and quaint villages like Dürnstein. Stop to taste local Rieslings and apricot liqueurs at a family-run winery. Capture photos of the Danube’s serene beauty, framed by rolling landscapes.'),(99,20,5,'Mozart Concert','Attend a Mozart concert in a historic Viennese venue, with costumed musicians performing classics like The Magic Flute. Learn about Mozart’s life in Vienna during a pre-concert talk. Dine on schnitzel at a traditional restaurant, reflecting on the evening’s elegance.'),(100,20,6,'Prater & Danube Island','Ride the iconic Riesenrad Ferris wheel in Prater Park, enjoying views of Vienna’s skyline. Explore Danube Island, cycling or walking along its trails and beaches. End with a picnic by the river, savoring Viennese pastries in the fresh air.'),(101,21,1,'Mirabell Gardens','Visit Mirabell Gardens, a Baroque gem featured in The Sound of Music, with its Pegasus Fountain and rose gardens. Tour the Sound of Music filming sites, including the gazebo and Nonnberg Abbey. Enjoy a coffee at a nearby café, soaking in Salzburg’s musical legacy.'),(102,21,2,'Mozart’s Birthplace','Explore Mozart’s Birthplace, a museum showcasing the composer’s early life, instruments, and manuscripts. Wander Salzburg’s charming Getreidegasse, lined with historic shops and wrought-iron signs. Savor a Mozartkugel chocolate and lunch at a traditional Austrian gasthaus.'),(103,21,3,'Hohensalzburg Fortress','Tour Hohensalzburg Fortress, a medieval stronghold with panoramic views of Salzburg and the Alps. Explore its princely chambers, armory, and marionette museum. End with a dinner of tafelspitz, enjoying the fortress’s illuminated silhouette against the night sky.'),(104,22,1,'Sound of Music Tour','Embark on a Sound of Music tour, visiting Mirabell Gardens, Schloss Leopoldskron, and the Mondsee wedding church. Sing along to the film’s iconic songs while learning about its production. Savor a lunch of schnitzel at a lakeside restaurant, surrounded by alpine scenery.'),(105,22,2,'Hohensalzburg & Getreidegasse','Explore Hohensalzburg Fortress, wandering its Gothic halls and enjoying views of the Salzach River. Stroll Getreidegasse, shopping for local crafts and sampling Austrian pastries. Dine at a historic beer hall, trying hearty dishes like goulash with dumplings.'),(106,22,3,'Hallstatt Day Trip','Visit Hallstatt, a postcard-perfect village nestled between mountains and a serene lake. Tour the ancient salt mine and the Gothic St. Michael’s Church with its unique bone house. Enjoy a lakeside lunch of fresh trout, capturing photos of this UNESCO World Heritage site.'),(107,22,4,'Berchtesgaden & Eagle’s Nest','Journey to Berchtesgaden, exploring the Eagle’s Nest, a historic mountaintop retreat with stunning Alpine views. Visit the town’s royal castle and salt mines, steeped in Bavarian history. Savor a Bavarian pretzel and weissbier at a local biergarten.'),(108,22,5,'Salzburg Cathedral','Tour Salzburg Cathedral, admiring its Baroque dome and ornate frescoes, where Mozart was baptized. Visit the Residenz Palace, with its lavish staterooms and art gallery. Relax with a coffee in Kapitelplatz, watching horse-drawn carriages pass by.'),(109,22,6,'Hellbrunn Palace','Explore Hellbrunn Palace, famous for its trick fountains that playfully spray visitors in its whimsical gardens. Tour the palace’s ornate rooms and the nearby Salzburg Zoo. End with a farewell dinner of apfelstrudel, celebrating Salzburg’s charm.'),(110,23,1,'Alexander Nevsky Cathedral','Visit the Alexander Nevsky Cathedral, marveling at its golden domes and intricate frescoes, a symbol of Sofia. Explore the crypt’s icon museum, showcasing Bulgaria’s Orthodox art. Enjoy a traditional banitsa breakfast at a nearby café, soaking in the city’s vibrant energy.'),(111,23,2,'Vitosha Boulevard','Stroll Vitosha Boulevard, Sofia’s lively pedestrian street, lined with chic boutiques, cafés, and street musicians. Visit the nearby National Palace of Culture, browsing its art exhibitions and modern architecture. Savor a lunch of shopska salad, with views of Vitosha Mountain in the distance.'),(112,23,3,'National History Museum','Tour the National History Museum, discovering Bulgaria’s ancient Thracian treasures and medieval artifacts. Explore the museum’s lush park, once a communist-era residence. End with a rakia tasting at a local tavern, embracing Sofia’s rich cultural heritage.'),(113,24,1,'Alexander Nevsky & Sofia Center','Admire the Alexander Nevsky Cathedral’s neo-Byzantine splendor and its vast icon collection. Wander Sofia’s center, visiting the Rotunda of St. George and the lively Serdika ruins. Enjoy a lunch of kebapche at a traditional mehana, immersed in Sofia’s historic heart.'),(114,24,2,'Rila Monastery','Journey to Rila Monastery, a UNESCO site with vibrant frescoes and a serene mountain setting. Explore the monastery’s museum, showcasing ancient manuscripts and religious relics. Savor a monk-made yogurt lunch, surrounded by the Rila Mountains’ tranquil beauty.'),(115,24,3,'Plovdiv Old Town','Explore Plovdiv’s Old Town, wandering cobblestone streets lined with colorful 19th-century houses and Roman ruins. Visit the Ancient Theatre and Ethnographic Museum, steeped in Bulgarian culture. Dine on kavarma in a historic restaurant, enjoying Plovdiv’s bohemian vibe.'),(116,24,4,'Thracian Tombs','Visit the Thracian Tombs of Kazanlak, a UNESCO site with intricate frescoes depicting ancient rituals. Explore the nearby Rose Valley, learning about Bulgaria’s rose oil production. Savor a rose-flavored dessert at a local café, reflecting on the region’s ancient heritage.'),(117,24,5,'Boyana Church','Tour the Boyana Church, a medieval gem with 13th-century frescoes, a UNESCO World Heritage site. Wander the surrounding forest trails, enjoying views of Sofia from the foothills. Relax with a coffee at a nearby café, appreciating the church’s serene setting.'),(118,24,6,'Vitosha Mountain Hike','Hike Vitosha Mountain’s scenic trails, passing waterfalls and panoramic viewpoints over Sofia. Visit the Dragalevtsi Monastery, a hidden gem nestled in the forest. Enjoy a picnic lunch of lutenitsa and bread, soaking in the mountain’s fresh air.'),(119,24,7,'Sofia Food Tour','Embark on a guided food tour, tasting Bulgarian specialties like tarator, moussaka, and rakia in Sofia’s vibrant eateries. Visit local markets to sample cheeses and cured meats, learning about Bulgarian culinary traditions. End with a farewell dinner in a lively tavern, celebrating Sofia’s flavors.'),(120,25,1,'Sea Garden & Beach','Stroll Varna’s Sea Garden, a lush park with flowerbeds, fountains, and sea views, perfect for a morning walk. Relax on Varna’s sandy beaches, swimming in the Black Sea or trying water sports. Enjoy a seafood lunch at a beachfront restaurant, savoring fresh mussels and local wine.'),(121,25,2,'Archaeological Museum','Visit Varna’s Archaeological Museum, home to the world’s oldest gold treasure and Thracian artifacts. Explore exhibits on ancient Bulgarian history, from Roman baths to medieval jewelry. Savor a coffee in the museum’s courtyard, reflecting on Varna’s ancient past.'),(122,25,3,'Aladzha Monastery','Explore the Aladzha Monastery, a rock-hewn complex carved into cliffs, with medieval frescoes and caves. Hike the surrounding forest trails for views of the Black Sea coast. End with a picnic lunch in the monastery’s serene setting, embracing Varna’s natural beauty.'),(123,26,1,'Sea Garden & Varna Cathedral','Wander Varna’s Sea Garden, enjoying its open-air theater and dolphinarium amidst lush greenery. Visit the Varna Cathedral, with its golden domes and vibrant frescoes, a city landmark. Savor a lunch of grilled fish by the sea, soaking in the coastal ambiance.'),(124,26,2,'Balchik Palace','Tour the Balchik Palace, a romantic seaside retreat with elegant architecture and exotic botanical gardens. Stroll the terraced gardens, featuring cacti, roses, and sea views. Enjoy a wine tasting of local varietals, relaxing in the palace’s serene courtyard.'),(125,26,3,'Nessebar Day Trip','Explore Nessebar, a UNESCO-listed town with ancient churches and cobblestone streets on a Black Sea peninsula. Visit the Church of Christ Pantocrator and archaeological museum, steeped in history. Dine on fresh calamari at a seaside taverna, watching waves lap the shore.'),(126,26,4,'Cape Kaliakra','Visit Cape Kaliakra’s dramatic cliffs, exploring its medieval fortress ruins and legends of heroic battles. Spot dolphins in the Black Sea from the cape’s scenic lookout points. Savor a picnic lunch of Bulgarian cheeses, enjoying the rugged coastal beauty.'),(127,26,5,'Archaeological Museum','Discover Varna’s Archaeological Museum, showcasing ancient gold artifacts and Roman mosaics in a grand 19th-century building. Join a guided tour to learn about the region’s Thracian and Greek heritage. Relax with a coffee in Varna’s lively center, reflecting on the day’s discoveries.'),(128,26,6,'Dolphinarium & Beach','Watch a playful dolphin show at Varna’s Dolphinarium, a family-friendly highlight in the Sea Garden. Spend the afternoon on the beach, swimming or lounging under colorful umbrellas. End with a farewell dinner of Black Sea fish, celebrating Varna’s coastal charm.'),(129,27,1,'Gamla Stan','Wander Gamla Stan’s cobblestone streets, exploring colorful buildings, the Royal Palace, and the Nobel Prize Museum. Visit Storkyrkan Cathedral, admiring its Baroque interiors and historic statues. Savor a fika (coffee and pastry break) at a cozy café, soaking in Stockholm’s medieval charm.'),(130,27,2,'Vasa Museum','Tour the Vasa Museum, marveling at the preserved 17th-century warship, a marvel of maritime history. Explore interactive exhibits on the ship’s sinking and recovery, bringing the past to life. Enjoy a lunch of Swedish meatballs at the museum restaurant, with views of the harbor.'),(131,27,3,'City Hall & Nobel Tour','Visit Stockholm City Hall, climbing its tower for panoramic views and exploring the Golden Hall’s mosaics. Learn about the Nobel Prize during a guided tour, imagining the annual banquet. Stroll the waterfront, savoring a cinnamon bun from a nearby bakery.'),(132,27,4,'Skansen Open-Air Museum','Explore Skansen, the world’s first open-air museum, with historic farmhouses, artisan workshops, and Nordic animals like reindeer. Watch traditional Swedish folk dances and try glassblowing or baking. End with a picnic lunch in Skansen’s gardens, enjoying Stockholm’s serene island setting.'),(133,28,1,'Gamla Stan & Royal Palace','Discover Gamla Stan’s medieval charm, visiting the Royal Palace’s royal apartments and Treasury. Explore hidden alleys and the lively Stortorget square, framed by colorful facades. Savor a lunch of gravlax at a historic restaurant, immersed in Stockholm’s vibrant heart.'),(134,28,2,'Vasa & Nordic Museums','Marvel at the Vasa Museum’s massive warship, learning about its 1628 voyage through interactive displays. Visit the Nordic Museum, showcasing Swedish cultural history with folk art and Viking artifacts. Enjoy a coffee by the waterfront, watching ferries crisscross the harbor.'),(135,28,3,'Sandhamn Island','Cruise to Sandhamn in Stockholm’s archipelago, exploring its sandy beaches and quaint wooden houses. Hike scenic trails or swim in the Baltic Sea’s crisp waters. Savor a seafood lunch at a harborside restaurant, soaking in the island’s tranquil beauty.'),(136,28,4,'Drottningholm Palace','Tour Drottningholm Palace, a UNESCO site with Baroque gardens, a Chinese Pavilion, and a historic theater. Stroll the palace grounds, admiring fountains and manicured hedges. Enjoy a fika with kanelbullar (cinnamon buns) at the palace café, reflecting on Sweden’s royal heritage.'),(137,28,5,'ABBA Museum','Dive into the ABBA Museum, singing along to hits and exploring interactive exhibits on the band’s global fame. Try on virtual ABBA costumes and record your own performance in the studio. Savor a retro-inspired lunch at the museum café, dancing to 70s tunes.'),(138,28,6,'Djurgården & Canal Cruise','Relax in Djurgården’s green spaces, visiting the lush Rosendals Trädgård gardens and café. Embark on a canal cruise, gliding under Stockholm’s bridges and past historic buildings. End with a dinner of elk steak at a Djurgården restaurant, celebrating Sweden’s natural beauty.'),(139,28,7,'Fotografiska Museum','Explore Fotografiska, a cutting-edge photography museum with thought-provoking exhibits by global artists. Wander the waterfront, enjoying views of Stockholm’s skyline and passing ships. Savor a farewell dinner of Nordic cuisine, reflecting on your archipelago adventure.'),(140,29,1,'Haga District','Stroll Gothenburg’s Haga district, with its charming wooden houses, cozy cafés, and boutique shops. Visit Haga Nygata, sampling giant cinnamon buns at a historic bakery. Savor a lunch of shrimp smörgås, soaking in the neighborhood’s laid-back Scandinavian vibe.'),(141,29,2,'Universeum Science Center','Explore the Universeum, with its rainforest exhibit, aquariums, and hands-on science experiments for all ages. Walk through the tropical zone, spotting sloths and colorful birds. Enjoy a coffee at the center’s café, discussing the day’s interactive discoveries.'),(142,29,3,'Fish Market & Archipelago','Visit Feskekôrka, Gothenburg’s fish market, browsing fresh seafood and local delicacies in a church-like hall. Embark on a short archipelago cruise, exploring islands like Styrsö with their quaint fishing villages. Savor a seafood platter at a harborside restaurant, celebrating Gothenburg’s maritime heritage.'),(143,30,1,'Haga & Slottsskogen','Wander Haga’s picturesque streets, shopping for Swedish crafts and enjoying a fika with cardamom buns. Explore Slottsskogen Park, with its free zoo, penguin pond, and scenic trails. Savor a lunch of västkuströra (seafood salad) at a park café, immersed in Gothenburg’s green heart.'),(144,30,2,'Marstrand Island','Journey to Marstrand, a historic island with the imposing Carlsten Fortress and charming yacht-filled harbor. Hike coastal trails for views of the Kattegat Sea and rocky cliffs. Enjoy a lobster lunch at a seaside restaurant, soaking in the island’s maritime charm.'),(145,30,3,'Fjällbacka Coastal Village','Visit Fjällbacka, a picturesque fishing village with red boathouses and dramatic granite cliffs, featured in Camilla Läckberg’s novels. Kayak along the coast or explore the village’s quaint shops and cafés. Savor a dinner of fresh cod, watching the sunset over the archipelago.'),(146,30,4,'Liseberg Amusement Park','Spend a fun-filled day at Liseberg, riding thrilling roller coasters and enjoying classic carnival games. Explore the park’s lush gardens and catch a live concert or show. Indulge in cotton candy and a burger at a park eatery, embracing the festive atmosphere.'),(147,30,5,'Gothenburg Archipelago','Cruise Gothenburg’s southern archipelago, visiting car-free islands like Brännö for cycling and swimming. Explore rocky beaches and traditional fishing huts, learning about local life. Savor a picnic lunch of smoked shrimp, surrounded by the archipelago’s serene beauty.'),(148,30,6,'Museum of World Culture','Tour the Museum of World Culture, with its thought-provoking exhibits on global traditions and contemporary issues. Participate in a workshop, perhaps learning about indigenous art or music. End with a farewell dinner of Swedish herring, celebrating Gothenburg’s coastal culture.'),(149,31,1,'Giza Pyramids & Sphinx','Explore the Giza Pyramids, marveling at the Great Pyramid of Khufu and climbing inside its ancient chambers. Visit the Great Sphinx, learning about its enigmatic history and pharaonic significance. Enjoy a camel ride across the desert plateau, capturing iconic photos at sunset.'),(150,31,2,'Egyptian Museum','Tour the Egyptian Museum in Tahrir Square, admiring treasures like Tutankhamun’s golden mask and colossal statues. Join a guided tour to uncover stories of pharaohs, mummies, and ancient rituals. Savor a koshari lunch at a nearby café, soaking in Cairo’s bustling energy.'),(151,31,3,'Khan el-Khalili Bazaar','Wander Khan el-Khalili’s vibrant alleys, shopping for spices, jewelry, and handcrafted lanterns in a historic market. Visit the ancient Al-Hussein Mosque and sip mint tea at a traditional ahwa (coffeehouse). Savor a dinner of stuffed pigeon, immersed in the bazaar’s lively atmosphere.'),(152,32,1,'Giza Pyramids & Sphinx','Discover the Giza Pyramids, exploring the ancient wonders of Khufu, Khafre, and Menkaure with a guided tour. Photograph the Great Sphinx, its lion’s body and pharaoh’s face glowing in the desert sun. Enjoy a Bedouin-style lunch at a nearby camp, with views of the plateau.'),(153,32,2,'Saqqara & Dashur','Visit Saqqara’s Step Pyramid of Djoser, the world’s oldest stone monument, and explore its surrounding tombs. Tour Dashur’s Bent and Red Pyramids, marveling at their unique shapes and serene desert setting. Savor a falafel lunch at a local eatery, reflecting on Egypt’s architectural genius.'),(154,32,3,'Egyptian Museum','Explore the Egyptian Museum’s vast collection, from royal mummies to the treasures of the Amarna period. Admire intricate jewelry and sarcophagi, guided by an Egyptologist’s insights. Relax with a hibiscus tea at a nearby café, discussing the day’s pharaonic discoveries.'),(155,32,4,'Coptic Cairo','Tour Coptic Cairo’s ancient sites, including the Hanging Church with its wooden roof and the Ben Ezra Synagogue. Visit the Coptic Museum, showcasing early Christian art and manuscripts. Savor a lunch of molokhia at a traditional restaurant, immersed in this historic enclave.'),(156,32,5,'Khan el-Khalili & Islamic Cairo','Explore Islamic Cairo, visiting the Citadel’s Mohamed Ali Mosque with its alabaster walls and sweeping city views. Wander Khan el-Khalili, bargaining for perfumes and papyrus art in its bustling souks. Enjoy a shisha session at a historic coffeehouse, soaking in the medieval ambiance.'),(157,32,6,'Citadel & Mohamed Ali Mosque','Revisit the Citadel, exploring its military museum and the Gawhara Palace’s opulent interiors. Admire the Mohamed Ali Mosque’s Ottoman-inspired domes and minarets, a Cairo landmark. Savor a koshari dinner in a lively downtown eatery, reflecting on Cairo’s layered history.'),(158,32,7,'Nile Dinner Cruise','Embark on a Nile River dinner cruise, enjoying Egyptian cuisine like stuffed vine leaves while passing Cairo’s illuminated skyline. Watch a traditional tanoura dance and belly dancing performance on board. Toast to your journey with a glass of hibiscus juice, gliding under starry skies.'),(159,33,1,'Bibliotheca Alexandrina','Tour the Bibliotheca Alexandrina, a modern marvel with its slanted roof and vast library inspired by its ancient predecessor. Explore its planetarium, manuscripts museum, and art galleries, showcasing Egypt’s intellectual heritage. Savor a seafood lunch by the Mediterranean, enjoying harbor views.'),(160,33,2,'Qaitbay Citadel','Visit the Qaitbay Citadel, a 15th-century fortress on the site of the ancient Lighthouse of Alexandria, with stunning sea views. Wander its stone ramparts and maritime museum, learning about its Mamluk history. Relax with a coffee at a seaside café, watching fishing boats bob in the harbor.'),(161,33,3,'Montazah Palace Gardens','Stroll the Montazah Palace Gardens, a lush oasis with manicured lawns, exotic trees, and a Victorian-style palace. Relax on Montazah’s private beaches, swimming in the Mediterranean’s turquoise waters. Enjoy a picnic lunch under palm trees, soaking in Alexandria’s coastal serenity.'),(162,34,1,'Bibliotheca Alexandrina','Explore the Bibliotheca Alexandrina’s futuristic architecture, browsing its rare books and digital archives. Visit the Antiquities Museum, showcasing Greco-Roman artifacts from Alexandria’s past. Savor a lunch of grilled calamari at a waterfront restaurant, overlooking the Eastern Harbor.'),(163,34,2,'Qaitbay & Roman Amphitheatre','Tour the Qaitbay Citadel, climbing its towers for panoramic views of the Mediterranean and Alexandria’s skyline. Visit the Roman Amphitheatre, a well-preserved site with marble seats and mosaics. Savor a shawarma lunch in the nearby Kom el-Dikka district, immersed in history.'),(164,34,3,'Rosetta Day Trip','Journey to Rosetta, exploring its Ottoman-era mansions and the Rosetta Stone discovery site at Fort Julien. Cruise the Nile Delta’s waterways, spotting birdlife and traditional fishing boats. Enjoy a lunch of fresh fish in a riverside restaurant, embracing Rosetta’s tranquil charm.'),(165,34,4,'El Alamein War Museum','Visit the El Alamein War Museum, learning about the WWII battles through tanks, artifacts, and memorials. Tour the Commonwealth and German cemeteries, reflecting on the region’s wartime history. Savor a light lunch at a nearby café, enjoying views of the Mediterranean coast.'),(166,34,5,'Pompey’s Pillar','Explore Pompey’s Pillar, a towering Roman column surrounded by the Serapeum’s ancient ruins and sphinxes. Descend into the Catacombs of Kom el-Shoqafa, a haunting blend of Egyptian and Greco-Roman art. Savor a dinner of Alexandrian liver sandwiches, a local street food favorite.'),(167,34,6,'Montazah & Corniche','Relax in Montazah Palace Gardens, strolling through rosebeds and palm-lined paths with sea breezes. Walk the Corniche, Alexandria’s scenic waterfront, passing historic cafés and Art Deco buildings. End with a farewell dinner of seafood mezze, celebrating Alexandria’s Mediterranean allure.'),(168,35,1,'Hassan II Mosque','Tour the Hassan II Mosque, a stunning masterpiece with its minaret soaring over the Atlantic and intricate zellige tilework. Explore the mosque’s vast courtyard and prayer hall, built partially over the ocean. Savor a mint tea at a nearby café, enjoying views of the crashing waves.'),(169,35,2,'Old Medina & Rick’s Café','Wander Casablanca’s Old Medina, browsing bustling souks for spices, leather goods, and traditional kaftans. Visit Rick’s Café, a re-creation of the iconic Casablanca film setting, for a nostalgic lunch. Stroll the medina’s narrow alleys, discovering hidden mosques and colonial-era buildings.'),(170,35,3,'Corniche & Morocco Mall','Stroll the Ain Diab Corniche, a lively promenade with beach clubs, cafés, and Atlantic views. Shop at the Morocco Mall, a luxurious complex with designer stores and an aquarium. Savor a dinner of tagine at a seaside restaurant, watching the sunset over the ocean.'),(171,36,1,'Hassan II Mosque','Visit the Hassan II Mosque, admiring its hand-carved marble and retractable roof, a marvel of Moroccan craftsmanship. Tour the museum to learn about its construction and cultural significance. Enjoy a coffee by the Atlantic, watching worshippers and tourists mingle in the courtyard.'),(172,36,2,'Old Medina & Habous','Explore Casablanca’s Old Medina, haggling for jewelry and ceramics in its lively souks. Visit the Habous Quarter, with its neo-Moorish architecture, bookstores, and patisseries. Savor a lunch of couscous at a traditional eatery, soaking in the quarter’s colonial charm.'),(173,36,3,'Rabat Day Trip','Journey to Rabat, touring the Hassan Tower and the ornate Mausoleum of Mohammed V. Wander the Kasbah of the Udayas, with its blue-and-white streets and Andalusian gardens. Enjoy a lunch of rfissa, a Moroccan chicken dish, in a historic riad overlooking the Bou Regreg River.'),(174,36,4,'Tangier Excursion','Explore Tangier’s medina, with its labyrinthine alleys, Grand Socco, and historic Kasbah Museum. Visit Cape Spartel, where the Atlantic meets the Mediterranean, and the Caves of Hercules. Savor a seafood tagine at a cliffside restaurant, enjoying Tangier’s vibrant coastal vibe.'),(175,36,5,'Asilah Coastal Town','Visit Asilah, a charming coastal town with whitewashed walls, colorful murals, and a relaxed medina. Stroll the Portuguese ramparts for Atlantic views and browse local art galleries. Savor a lunch of grilled sardines, embracing Asilah’s artistic and maritime heritage.'),(176,36,6,'Corniche & Anfa District','Walk the Ain Diab Corniche, enjoying ice cream and ocean breezes amidst joggers and families. Explore the upscale Anfa district, with its Art Deco villas and trendy cafés. Savor a dinner of pastilla, a sweet-savory pastry, at a chic Casablanca restaurant.'),(177,36,7,'Moroccan Cooking Class','Join a Moroccan cooking class, learning to prepare dishes like lamb tagine and harissa-spiced salads with a local chef. Shop for ingredients at a nearby market, discovering Moroccan spices and produce. Feast on your creations in a traditional riad, celebrating Morocco’s rich flavors.'),(178,37,1,'Jemaa el-Fnaa','Dive into Jemaa el-Fnaa, Marrakesh’s vibrant square, with snake charmers, storytellers, and food stalls serving tanjia. Explore the nearby Koutoubia Mosque, admiring its 12th-century minaret and gardens. Savor a mint tea at a rooftop café, watching the square’s lively spectacle unfold.'),(179,37,2,'Bahia Palace','Tour the Bahia Palace, marveling at its intricate stucco work, zellige tiles, and lush courtyards filled with orange trees. Wander the adjacent Mellah, the historic Jewish quarter, with its spice markets and synagogue. Savor a lunch of chicken tagine, immersed in Marrakesh’s cultural mosaic.'),(180,37,3,'Majorelle Garden','Visit the Majorelle Garden, a serene oasis with cobalt-blue buildings, exotic plants, and a Berber museum. Explore the nearby Yves Saint Laurent Museum, showcasing the designer’s iconic fashion. Relax with a coffee at the garden café, surrounded by bamboo and cacti.'),(181,37,4,'Souk Shopping','Navigate Marrakesh’s souks, bargaining for lanterns, rugs, and leather goods in a maze of colorful stalls. Visit the Souk des Teinturiers to see traditional dye workshops and vibrant fabrics. Savor a farewell dinner of mechoui (roasted lamb), celebrating your souk adventure.'),(182,38,1,'Jemaa el-Fnaa & Koutoubia','Explore Jemaa el-Fnaa’s bustling market, sampling fresh orange juice and watching acrobats perform. Visit the Koutoubia Mosque, with its Almohad architecture and serene gardens. Savor a lunch of bessara soup at a rooftop restaurant, overlooking Marrakesh’s vibrant heart.'),(183,38,2,'Bahia & El Badi Palaces','Tour the Bahia Palace’s opulent halls and tranquil courtyards, a masterpiece of Moroccan design. Visit El Badi Palace, with its sunken gardens and remnants of 16th-century grandeur. Savor a mint tea in the palace’s ruins, imagining its former splendor.'),(184,38,3,'Ouarzazate & Ait Benhaddou','Journey to Ouarzazate, visiting its film studios and the UNESCO-listed Ait Benhaddou, a fortified ksar with mud-brick architecture. Explore the kasbah’s winding alleys, featured in films like Gladiator. Savor a lunch of Berber omelets, surrounded by the desert’s dramatic landscapes.'),(185,38,4,'Atlas Mountains Trek','Trek through the Atlas Mountains, passing Berber villages, terraced fields, and the stunning Imlil Valley. Visit a traditional mud-brick home, learning about local customs over mint tea. Savor a tagine lunch in a mountain guesthouse, with views of snow-capped peaks.'),(186,38,5,'Majorelle & Menara Gardens','Stroll the Majorelle Garden’s vibrant pathways, admiring its art deco villa and rare plants. Visit the Menara Gardens, with its olive groves and reflective pavilion by a serene lake. Savor a lunch of zaalouk salad, relaxing in the gardens’ tranquil ambiance.'),(187,38,6,'Saadian Tombs','Explore the Saadian Tombs, a hidden 16th-century necropolis with ornate stucco and marble mausoleums. Wander the nearby Kasbah district, browsing local crafts and historic mosques. Savor a dinner of couscous royale, celebrating Marrakesh’s royal heritage.'),(188,38,7,'Moroccan Hammam','Relax in a traditional Moroccan hammam, enjoying a steam bath, exfoliating scrub, and soothing massage. Learn about the hammam’s cultural significance from a local guide. Savor a farewell lunch of harira soup, reflecting on your Marrakesh journey in a serene riad.'),(189,39,1,'Apartheid Museum','Explore the Apartheid Museum, with its powerful exhibits on South Africa’s history of segregation and resistance. Walk through immersive displays, including Mandela’s prison cell replica and protest footage. Savor a lunch of bunny chow, reflecting on the museum’s emotional impact.'),(190,39,2,'Soweto Tour','Tour Soweto, visiting Vilakazi Street, the only street with homes of two Nobel laureates, Mandela and Tutu. Explore the Hector Pieterson Memorial, commemorating the 1976 uprising. Savor a traditional kota sandwich at a local eatery, immersed in Soweto’s vibrant community.'),(191,39,3,'Constitution Hill','Visit Constitution Hill, touring the Old Fort and the Constitutional Court, symbols of South Africa’s democracy. Explore exhibits on political prisoners and human rights struggles. Savor a braai (barbecue) lunch, celebrating Johannesburg’s journey to freedom.'),(192,40,1,'Apartheid Museum','Discover the Apartheid Museum’s moving exhibits, from pass laws to the Soweto Uprising, with a guided tour. Engage with interactive displays, including personal stories of resilience and reconciliation. Savor a lunch of pap and chakalaka, reflecting on South Africa’s complex history.'),(193,40,2,'Soweto & Mandela House','Explore Soweto’s vibrant streets, visiting Mandela House, where Nelson Mandela lived before his imprisonment. Tour the Regina Mundi Church, a hub of anti-apartheid activism. Savor a shisa nyama (grilled meat) lunch, mingling with locals in Soweto’s lively atmosphere.'),(194,40,3,'Kruger National Park Safari','Embark on a safari in Kruger National Park, spotting the Big Five (lion, elephant, buffalo, leopard, rhino) in their natural habitat. Enjoy guided game drives through savannah and bushveld, learning about wildlife conservation. Savor a bush braai dinner under the stars, surrounded by the sounds of the wild.'),(195,40,4,'Kruger Game Drives','Continue your Kruger adventure with morning and evening game drives, tracking cheetahs, giraffes, and rare birds. Visit a waterhole to observe hippos and crocodiles in action. Relax with a sundowner drink at a scenic lookout, sharing safari stories with fellow travelers.'),(196,40,5,'Lion Park','Visit the Lion Park near Johannesburg, interacting with lion cubs and joining a guided tour to see cheetahs and hyenas. Take a self-drive safari through the park’s enclosures, spotting antelopes and zebras. Savor a lunch of boerewors rolls, enjoying the park’s family-friendly vibe.'),(197,40,6,'Cradle of Humankind','Explore the Cradle of Humankind, touring the Sterkfontein Caves, where ancient hominid fossils like Mrs. Ples were found. Visit the Maropeng Visitor Centre for exhibits on human evolution. Savor a lunch of malva pudding, reflecting on humanity’s origins in this UNESCO site.'),(198,40,7,'Johannesburg City Tour','Tour Johannesburg’s Maboneng Precinct, a trendy hub of street art, galleries, and artisanal markets. Visit the Carlton Centre’s Top of Africa for panoramic city views. Savor a farewell dinner of Cape Malay curry, celebrating Jo’burg’s dynamic culture and history.'),(199,41,1,'Table Mountain & City Bowl','Ascend Table Mountain via cable car, marveling at panoramic views of Cape Town’s coastline and the Twelve Apostles. Wander the vibrant Company’s Garden, exploring historic sites like the South African Museum and colorful Bo-Kaap neighborhood. Savor a lunch of bobotie at a local eatery, soaking in the city’s multicultural vibe.'),(200,41,2,'V&A Waterfront & Robben Island','Explore the bustling V&A Waterfront, shopping for crafts and watching street performers by the harbor. Take a ferry to Robben Island, touring Nelson Mandela’s former prison cell with a guide who shares stories of resilience. Enjoy a seafood dinner at a waterfront restaurant, with views of Table Bay sparkling at dusk.'),(201,41,3,'Cape Point & Penguins','Journey to Cape Point, hiking to the lighthouse for breathtaking views where the Atlantic and Indian Oceans meet. Visit Boulders Beach, watching playful African penguins waddle along the sandy shores. Savor a fish and chips lunch at Simon’s Town, reflecting on the Cape’s wild beauty.'),(202,42,1,'Table Mountain & Kirstenbosch','Ride the cable car to Table Mountain’s summit, capturing photos of Cape Town’s dramatic coastline and distant peaks. Stroll Kirstenbosch Botanical Gardens, admiring rare fynbos plants and the tree canopy walkway. Enjoy a picnic lunch amidst the gardens, surrounded by the sounds of birds and rustling leaves.'),(203,42,2,'Robben Island & Waterfront','Visit Robben Island, exploring its haunting prison museum and Mandela’s cell with a former inmate guide. Wander the V&A Waterfront, browsing artisanal markets and savoring a coffee by the marina. Dine on Cape Malay curry at a harborside restaurant, watching ships glide into the sunset.'),(204,42,3,'Cape Point & Chapman’s Peak','Drive along Chapman’s Peak, a scenic coastal road with cliffs plunging into the Atlantic. Explore Cape Point Nature Reserve, spotting ostriches and baboons while hiking to the iconic lighthouse. Savor a seafood platter at a Hout Bay restaurant, with waves crashing nearby.'),(205,42,4,'Stellenbosch Wine Tour','Tour Stellenbosch’s rolling vineyards, tasting award-winning Chenin Blanc and Pinotage at historic estates like Spier. Learn about South Africa’s winemaking heritage during a cellar tour, surrounded by oak barrels. Enjoy a gourmet lunch paired with wines, overlooking the vine-clad hills.'),(206,42,5,'Hermanus Whale Watching','Travel to Hermanus, embarking on a whale-watching cruise to spot southern right whales breaching off the coast. Stroll the cliffside paths, learning about marine conservation from local guides. Savor a lunch of fresh linefish, with ocean views and the sound of whale calls in the distance.'),(207,42,6,'Garden Route: Tsitsikamma','Journey to Tsitsikamma National Park, hiking the Suspension Bridge Trail over the Storms River’s dramatic gorge. Kayak through the park’s lush forests and rugged coastline, spotting otters and kingfishers. Enjoy a braai (barbecue) dinner under the stars, immersed in the Garden Route’s wild beauty.'),(208,42,7,'Bo-Kaap & City Culture','Explore Bo-Kaap’s colorful streets, visiting the Bo-Kaap Museum to learn about Cape Malay culture and history. Join a cooking class to prepare traditional dishes like samoosas and koeksisters. Savor your creations at a farewell dinner, celebrating Cape Town’s vibrant heritage.'),(209,43,1,'Nairobi National Park','Embark on a morning safari in Nairobi National Park, spotting lions, rhinos, and zebras against the city skyline. Visit the David Sheldrick Elephant Nursery, feeding and learning about orphaned elephants. Savor a lunch of nyama choma (grilled meat) at a local restaurant, reflecting on the morning’s wildlife encounters.'),(210,43,2,'Giraffe Centre & Karen Blixen','Visit the Giraffe Centre, feeding endangered Rothschild’s giraffes from a raised platform and learning about conservation. Tour the Karen Blixen Museum, exploring the Out of Africa author’s historic home and lush gardens. Enjoy a coffee at a nearby café, surrounded by the serene Ngong Hills.'),(211,43,3,'Bomas of Kenya & Markets','Experience Bomas of Kenya, watching traditional dances and music from Kenya’s diverse tribes in a vibrant cultural show. Browse the Maasai Market for beaded jewelry, carvings, and textiles, haggling with local artisans. Savor a farewell dinner of ugali and sukuma wiki, celebrating Nairobi’s rich culture.'),(212,44,1,'Nairobi National Park Safari','Kick off your adventure with a safari in Nairobi National Park, tracking giraffes and leopards with the city as a backdrop. Visit the Nairobi Snake Park, learning about Kenya’s reptiles and amphibians. Enjoy a lunch of kuku choma (grilled chicken), soaking in the park’s unique urban-wild contrast.'),(213,44,2,'Maasai Mara Game Drive','Travel to the Maasai Mara, embarking on a game drive to spot the Big Five amidst rolling savannahs. Watch wildebeest migrate across the Mara River, a thrilling spectacle guided by expert rangers. Savor a bush dinner under the stars, with the sounds of hyenas echoing in the distance.'),(214,44,3,'Maasai Mara Balloon Safari','Soar over the Maasai Mara in a hot air balloon, witnessing sunrise over herds of elephants and acacia-dotted plains. Enjoy a champagne breakfast in the bush, surrounded by the reserve’s untamed beauty. Spend the afternoon visiting a Maasai village, learning about their traditions and crafts.'),(215,44,4,'Amboseli National Park','Journey to Amboseli, photographing elephants and zebras with Mount Kilimanjaro’s snow-capped peak as a backdrop. Explore the park’s swamps and observation hill, spotting flamingos and hippos. Savor a lunch at a lodge, enjoying views of the mountain and grazing wildlife.'),(216,44,5,'Amboseli Game Drives','Continue exploring Amboseli with morning and evening game drives, tracking lions and cheetahs across open plains. Visit a local community project, learning about conservation and sustainable tourism. Relax with a sundowner drink, watching the sunset paint Kilimanjaro in golden hues.'),(217,44,6,'Karen Blixen & Giraffe Centre','Return to Nairobi, touring the Karen Blixen Museum to delve into Kenya’s colonial history and literary legacy. Feed giraffes at the Giraffe Centre, capturing photos from the treetop platform. Savor a dinner of Ethiopian-inspired doro wat, reflecting on Kenya’s diverse influences.'),(218,44,7,'Bomas & Nairobi Culture','Celebrate Kenya’s heritage at Bomas of Boma, enjoying performances of Luo, Kikuyu, and Kamba dances. Shop at the City Market for souvenirs like soapstone carvings and Maasai shukas. Savor a farewell feast of pilau rice and goat stew, toasting to your Kenyan adventure.'),(219,45,1,'Christuskirche & City Sights','Visit the iconic Christuskirche, a German Lutheran church with pink sandstone and panoramic city views. Wander Independence Avenue, exploring the vibrant Post Street Mall and its meteorite display. Savor a lunch of kapana (grilled beef) at a local market, soaking in Windhoek’s lively atmosphere.'),(220,45,2,'Independence Memorial & Alte Feste','Tour the Independence Memorial Museum, learning about Namibia’s struggle for freedom through vivid exhibits. Explore Alte Feste, a colonial fort turned museum with artifacts from Namibia’s past. Enjoy a coffee at a rooftop café, overlooking Windhoek’s blend of modern and historic architecture.'),(221,45,3,'Daan Viljoen Game Reserve','Embark on a guided hike in Daan Viljoen Game Reserve, spotting zebras, kudus, and rare birds in a tranquil bushveld. Relax by the reserve’s dam, enjoying a picnic lunch with views of rolling hills. Savor a farewell dinner of game meat like oryx, celebrating Windhoek’s natural beauty.'),(222,46,1,'Windhoek City Tour','Explore Windhoek’s landmarks, from the colorful Christuskirche to the bustling Namibia Crafts Centre for handmade jewelry. Visit the National Art Gallery, showcasing local artists and cultural heritage. Savor a lunch of biltong and vetkoek, immersed in the city’s relaxed vibe.'),(223,46,2,'Sossusvlei Dunes','Journey to Sossusvlei, climbing the towering red dunes of the Namib Desert, including the iconic Dune 45 at sunrise. Explore Deadvlei’s surreal clay pan, with its skeletal trees and stark beauty. Savor a picnic breakfast amidst the dunes, surrounded by the desert’s vast silence.'),(224,46,3,'Sesriem Canyon & Namib-Naukluft','Hike Sesriem Canyon, marveling at its eroded rock formations carved by ancient rivers. Drive through Namib-Naukluft National Park, spotting springbok and oryx in the arid landscape. Enjoy a starlit dinner at a desert lodge, with the Milky Way illuminating the night sky.'),(225,46,4,'Etosha National Park Safari','Embark on a safari in Etosha National Park, tracking elephants, lions, and rhinos around the park’s massive salt pan. Visit floodlit waterholes at night, watching hyenas and leopards emerge under the stars. Savor a bush braai, sharing stories of the day’s wildlife sightings.'),(226,46,5,'Etosha Game Drives','Continue exploring Etosha with game drives, spotting cheetahs and flamingos in the park’s diverse ecosystems. Learn about conservation efforts at a ranger-led talk near Okaukuejo Camp. Relax with a sundowner drink, watching giraffes silhouetted against the sunset.'),(227,46,6,'Twyfelfontein Rock Art','Visit Twyfelfontein, a UNESCO site with ancient San rock engravings depicting animals and hunters. Explore the nearby Organ Pipes and Burnt Mountain, geological wonders of the Damaraland region. Savor a lunch of traditional Namibian potjiekos, reflecting on the region’s ancient heritage.'),(228,46,7,'Windhoek Cultural Farewell','Return to Windhoek, visiting the Katutura Township to learn about local life and sample street food like fat cakes. Shop for souvenirs at the Namibia Crafts Centre, from baskets to gemstones. Savor a farewell dinner of game steak, toasting to Namibia’s wild beauty.'),(229,47,1,'Anse Lazio & Beach Day','Relax on Anse Lazio, Praslin’s pristine beach, swimming in turquoise waters and lounging under palm trees. Snorkel along the coral reefs, spotting colorful fish and sea turtles. Savor a Creole lunch of octopus curry at a beachside restaurant, with waves lapping nearby.'),(230,47,2,'Vallée de Mai & Fond Ferdinand','Explore Vallée de Mai, a UNESCO site on Praslin, hiking through lush forests to see the rare coco de mer palm. Visit Fond Ferdinand, spotting black parrots and endemic plants in a tranquil reserve. Savor a fruit smoothie at a local café, surrounded by the island’s tropical beauty.'),(231,47,3,'Morne Seychellois Hike','Hike Morne Seychellois National Park on Mahé, trekking through misty forests to panoramic viewpoints over Victoria. Spot pitcher plants and chameleons while learning about the park’s biodiversity. Enjoy a picnic lunch with ocean views, soaking in the Seychelles’ serene landscapes.'),(232,47,4,'Victoria City Tour','Wander Victoria’s colorful Sir Selwyn Clarke Market, shopping for spices, vanilla, and handmade crafts. Visit the Victoria Botanical Gardens, admiring giant tortoises and exotic orchids. Savor a farewell dinner of ladob, a sweet coconut dessert, celebrating the Seychelles’ island charm.'),(233,48,1,'Victoria & Beau Vallon','Explore Victoria’s vibrant market, haggling for fresh fish and tropical fruits in a bustling atmosphere. Relax on Beau Vallon Beach, trying paddleboarding or jet-skiing in the warm Indian Ocean. Savor a Creole dinner of fish curry, watching the sunset over Mahé’s coastline.'),(234,48,2,'Praslin & Anse Lazio','Ferry to Praslin, lounging on Anse Lazio’s powdery sands and snorkeling among vibrant coral reefs. Visit the Vallée de Mai, marveling at the towering coco de mer palms and rare wildlife. Enjoy a beachside lunch of grilled lobster, immersed in Praslin’s tropical paradise.'),(235,48,3,'La Digue Island','Cycle around La Digue, visiting Anse Source d’Argent, a stunning beach with granite b