nd the Shanghai History Museum at its base. Stroll the Riverside Promenade, watching barges glide along the Huangpu. Savor a farewell dinner of drunken chicken, celebrating Shanghai’s vibrant energy.'),(363,74,1,'The Bund & Nanjing Road','Walk The Bund, photographing its Art Deco buildings and Pudong’s glittering skyscrapers. Shop on Nanjing Road, browsing flagship stores and sampling street foods like scallion pancakes. Savor a dinner of hairy crab, enjoying Shanghai’s cosmopolitan vibe.'),(364,74,2,'Zhujiajiao Water Town','Visit Zhujiajiao, cruising its ancient canals and crossing stone bridges lined with teahouses. Explore the town’s Qing Dynasty post office and Kezhi Garden’s serene courtyards. Savor a lunch of lotus root stuffed with sticky rice, soaking in the water town’s timeless charm.'),(365,74,3,'Yu Garden & Jade Buddha','Tour Yu Garden, marveling at its dragon walls and tranquil lotus ponds. Visit the Jade Buddha Temple, admiring its serene statues carved from Burmese jade. Savor a dinner of red-braised pork, reflecting on Shanghai’s cultural treasures.'),(366,74,4,'Suzhou Gardens & Silk','Journey to Suzhou, touring the UNESCO-listed Lingering Garden with its intricate pavilions and rockeries. Visit a silk factory, learning about silk production from cocoon to fabric. Savor a lunch of Wuxi spareribs, surrounded by Suzhou’s classical beauty.'),(367,74,5,'Shanghai Museum & French Concession','Explore the Shanghai Museum, admiring ancient bronzes, calligraphy, and jade artifacts. Stroll the French Concession’s tree-lined streets, visiting trendy cafés and historic villas. Savor a dinner of spicy tan tan noodles, embracing Shanghai’s modern flair.'),(368,74,6,'Skyline Cruise & Farewell','Embark on a Huangpu River night cruise, marveling at Shanghai’s illuminated skyline and neon-lit bridges. Visit the Propaganda Poster Art Centre, exploring China’s 20th-century history. Savor a farewell dinner of beggar’s chicken, toasting to Shanghai’s dynamic spirit.'),(369,75,1,'India Gate & Rajpath','Visit India Gate, a majestic war memorial, and stroll Rajpath to admire the Rashtrapati Bhavan’s grand architecture. Explore the National Museum, showcasing India’s 5,000-year history with Indus Valley artifacts. Savor a lunch of butter chicken, soaking in Delhi’s imperial grandeur.'),(370,75,2,'Qutub Minar & Lotus Temple','Tour Qutub Minar, a 12th-century minaret with intricate carvings, and the ancient Iron Pillar. Visit the Lotus Temple, a Bahá’í house of worship shaped like a blooming flower. Savor a dinner of biryani, reflecting on Delhi’s architectural diversity.'),(371,75,3,'Chandni Chowk & Red Fort','Wander Chandni Chowk’s bustling lanes, sampling parathas and jalebi from street vendors. Tour the Red Fort, a Mughal masterpiece with red sandstone palaces and lush gardens. Savor a farewell lunch of kebabs, celebrating Delhi’s vibrant culture.'),(372,76,1,'India Gate & Humayun’s Tomb','Explore India Gate, laying a wreath and admiring its illuminated arches at dusk. Visit Humayun’s Tomb, a Mughal precursor to the Taj Mahal with symmetrical gardens. Savor a lunch of paneer tikka, immersed in Delhi’s historic splendor.'),(373,76,2,'Qutub Minar & Old Delhi','Tour Qutub Minar, climbing its steps for views of Delhi’s skyline and ancient ruins. Wander Old Delhi’s Jama Masjid, a grand mosque, and rickshaw through Chandni Chowk’s spice markets. Savor a dinner of mutton korma, soaking in the city’s Mughal heritage.'),(374,76,3,'Agra & Taj Mahal','Journey to Agra, marveling at the Taj Mahal’s white marble domes glowing in the sunrise. Tour Agra Fort, exploring its palaces and mosques with views of the Yamuna River. Savor a lunch of petha sweets, reflecting on the monument’s timeless beauty.'),(375,76,4,'Fatehpur Sikri','Visit Fatehpur Sikri, a UNESCO-listed Mughal city with the grand Buland Darwaza and marble tomb of Salim Chishti. Explore the deserted palaces, imagining royal life in the 16th century. Savor a dinner of dal makhani, surrounded by the site’s haunting grandeur.'),(376,76,5,'Jaipur’s Amber Fort','Travel to Jaipur, touring Amber Fort’s ornate halls and mirrored Sheesh Mahal overlooking the desert. Ride an elephant to the fort’s entrance, capturing photos of its golden sandstone walls. Savor a lunch of laal maas, embracing Rajasthan’s royal heritage.'),(377,76,6,'Jaipur City Palace & Hawa Mahal','Explore Jaipur’s City Palace, admiring its Peacock Gate and royal artifacts in the Mubarak Mahal. Visit Hawa Mahal, the Palace of Winds, with its intricate pink sandstone latticework. Savor a dinner of ghevar dessert, soaking in the Pink City’s vibrant charm.'),(378,76,7,'Delhi Markets & Farewell','Shop at Delhi’s Dilli Haat, bargaining for handicrafts, saris, and Rajasthani jewelry. Visit Lodhi Gardens, relaxing among Mughal tombs and blooming flowers. Savor a farewell dinner of tandoori platter, toasting to India’s Golden Triangle.'),(379,77,1,'Gateway of India & Colaba','Visit the Gateway of India, a grand arch overlooking Mumbai’s harbor, bustling with ferries and vendors. Wander Colaba’s lively streets, shopping for antiques and streetwear at Causeway. Savor a lunch of vada pav, soaking in Mumbai’s coastal energy.'),(380,77,2,'Elephanta Caves','Ferry to Elephanta Caves, exploring 7th-century rock-cut temples dedicated to Shiva with intricate carvings. Hike to Cannon Hill, enjoying views of the Arabian Sea and distant skyline. Savor a dinner of Goan fish curry, reflecting on Mumbai’s ancient heritage.'),(381,77,3,'Marine Drive & Bollywood','Stroll Marine Drive, Mumbai’s “Queen’s Necklace,” watching the sunset over the Arabian Sea. Join a Bollywood studio tour, watching live filming and dancing in a mock set. Savor a farewell lunch of pav bhaji, celebrating Mumbai’s cinematic spirit.'),(382,78,1,'Gateway & Mumbai Icons','Tour the Gateway of India, photographing its basalt arch and bustling harbor life. Visit Chhatrapati Shivaji Terminus, a Victorian Gothic masterpiece and UNESCO site. Savor a lunch of bhel puri, immersed in Mumbai’s vibrant street culture.'),(383,78,2,'Elephanta & Kanheri Caves','Sail to Elephanta Island, exploring its 7th-century rock-cut caves with towering Shiva sculptures and intricate carvings. Journey to Kanheri Caves in Sanjay Gandhi National Park, wandering through 2nd-century Buddhist monasteries carved into basalt cliffs. Savor a lunch of Maharashtrian thali, surrounded by the park’s lush greenery and monkey-filled trails.'),(384,78,3,'Ajanta Caves Day Trip','Travel to Ajanta Caves, a UNESCO site, marveling at 2nd-century BCE Buddhist rock-cut temples adorned with vibrant frescoes. Explore the horseshoe-shaped ravine, discovering hidden stupas and intricately painted murals depicting Jataka tales. Savor a dinner of misal pav, reflecting on the caves’ ancient artistry under the starry Deccan sky.'),(385,78,4,'Marine Drive & Bandra','Stroll Marine Drive’s crescent-shaped promenade, watching waves crash as Mumbai’s skyline sparkles at dusk. Explore Bandra’s trendy streets, visiting hip cafés and the vibrant street art of Chapel Road. Savor a dinner of butter garlic crab, soaking in Bandra’s bohemian coastal vibe.'),(386,78,5,'Sanjay Gandhi National Park','Hike Sanjay Gandhi National Park’s Shilonda Trail, spotting leopards, deer, and rare birds in a lush urban jungle. Visit the park’s Jain temple, a serene retreat with intricate marble carvings. Savor a picnic lunch by Tulsi Lake, enjoying the park’s tranquil escape from Mumbai’s bustle.'),(387,78,6,'Bollywood & Farewell','Tour a Bollywood studio in Film City, watching live shoots and dancing in a colorful set replica. Shop at Colaba Causeway for souvenirs like brass lamps and pashmina shawls. Savor a farewell dinner of chicken tikka masala, toasting to Mumbai’s cinematic and cultural allure.'),(388,79,1,'National Monument & Merdeka Square','Visit the National Monument (Monas), climbing to its observation deck for panoramic views of Jakarta’s skyline. Wander Merdeka Square, exploring the lush gardens and historic landmarks like the National Museum. Savor a lunch of nasi goreng, soaking in the city’s vibrant energy.'),(389,79,2,'Old Batavia & Sunda Kelapa','Explore Old Batavia’s colonial quarter, touring the Jakarta History Museum in a 17th-century Dutch building. Visit Sunda Kelapa Harbor, watching traditional pinisi schooners unload spices and timber. Savor a dinner of sate ayam, immersed in Jakarta’s maritime heritage.'),(390,79,3,'Istiqlal Mosque & Chinatown','Tour Istiqlal Mosque, Southeast Asia’s largest, admiring its minimalist dome and vast prayer hall. Wander Glodok, Jakarta’s Chinatown, sampling bakpao buns and browsing temple offerings. Savor a farewell lunch of gado-gado, celebrating Jakarta’s cultural mosaic.'),(391,80,1,'National Monument & Museums','Ascend the National Monument, capturing photos of Jakarta’s sprawling urban landscape from its golden flame. Tour the National Museum, admiring ancient Javanese artifacts and Hindu-Buddhist statues. Savor a lunch of rendang, immersed in Indonesia’s historic heart.'),(392,80,2,'Old Batavia & Maritime Museum','Wander Old Batavia, exploring colonial-era buildings like Café Batavia and the Wayang Museum’s puppet collection. Visit the Maritime Museum at Sunda Kelapa, learning about Indonesia’s seafaring traditions. Savor a dinner of ikan bakar, with the harbor’s wooden ships glowing at dusk.'),(393,80,3,'Borobudur Temple','Journey to Borobudur, a 9th-century Buddhist temple, climbing its stone terraces adorned with 2,672 relief panels. Watch sunrise illuminate the stupas, surrounded by misty volcanoes and rice fields. Savor a breakfast of bubur ayam, reflecting on the temple’s spiritual serenity.'),(394,80,4,'Yogyakarta & Prambanan','Explore Yogyakarta’s Kraton Palace, learning about Javanese royalty amidst intricate pavilions. Visit Prambanan, a Hindu temple complex with soaring spires dedicated to Shiva and Vishnu. Savor a lunch of gudeg, soaking in Yogya’s cultural richness.'),(395,80,5,'Thousand Islands Day Trip','Sail to the Thousand Islands, snorkeling at Pulau Bidadari’s coral reefs teeming with tropical fish. Relax on a pristine beach, sipping fresh coconut water under palm trees. Savor a seafood barbecue, enjoying the islands’ tranquil escape from Jakarta’s bustle.'),(396,80,6,'Taman Mini Indonesia','Tour Taman Mini Indonesia Indah, exploring miniature replicas of Indonesia’s 26 provinces and traditional houses. Watch a cultural performance of Balinese kecak dance or Sumatran plate dance. Savor a dinner of soto betawi, celebrating Indonesia’s diverse heritage.'),(397,80,7,'Jakarta Markets & Farewell','Shop at Pasar Baru, bargaining for batik textiles, spices, and handmade jewelry in Jakarta’s oldest market. Visit Ancol Dreamland, strolling its beachfront promenade with city views. Savor a farewell dinner of ayam taliwang, toasting to Java’s vibrant culture.'),(398,81,1,'Uluwatu Temple & Sunset','Visit Uluwatu Temple, perched on cliffs with panoramic Indian Ocean views, watching monkeys play among ancient stones. Enjoy a kecak dance performance at sunset, with firelit dancers chanting to epic Ramayana tales. Savor a dinner of babi guling, soaking in Bali’s spiritual ambiance.'),(399,81,2,'Tanah Lot & Jatiluwih','Tour Tanah Lot Temple, a seafront shrine glowing against crashing waves and vibrant sunsets. Explore Jatiluwih Rice Terraces, a UNESCO site, cycling through emerald fields and traditional villages. Savor a lunch of nasi campur, surrounded by Bali’s lush countryside.'),(400,81,3,'Kuta Beach & Seminyak','Relax on Kuta Beach, surfing gentle waves or lounging under colorful umbrellas with a Bintang beer. Wander Seminyak’s trendy streets, shopping for boho fashion and dining at chic cafés. Savor a dinner of grilled jimbaran seafood, with sand between your toes.'),(401,81,4,'Ubud Art & Markets','Explore Ubud’s art market, bargaining for silver jewelry, sarongs, and hand-carved masks. Visit the Ubud Palace, admiring its ornate Balinese architecture and lotus ponds. Savor a farewell lunch of bebek betutu, celebrating Bali’s cultural heart.'),(402,82,1,'Ubud Monkey Forest','Wander Ubud’s Sacred Monkey Forest, watching long-tailed macaques swing through banyan trees and ancient temples. Explore the forest’s moss-covered statues and serene lotus pond, steeped in Balinese mythology. Savor a lunch of sate lilit, surrounded by Ubud’s lush jungle ambiance.'),(403,82,2,'Tegalalang & Gunung Kawi','Cycle through Tegalalang Rice Terraces, marveling at emerald terraces carved into volcanic hills. Visit Gunung Kawi, an 11th-century temple complex with rock-cut shrines along the Pakerisan River. Savor a dinner of lawar, reflecting on Bali’s rural beauty.'),(404,82,3,'Uluwatu & Kecak Dance','Tour Uluwatu Temple, clinging to cliffs above crashing waves, with sweeping ocean vistas. Watch a kecak dance at sunset, mesmerized by rhythmic chants and fiery performances. Savor a dinner of pepes ikan, enjoying the temple’s dramatic coastal setting.'),(405,82,4,'Nusa Penida Adventure','Sail to Nusa Penida, visiting Kelingking Beach’s T-rex-shaped cliffs and turquoise lagoon below. Snorkel at Crystal Bay, swimming with manta rays and vibrant coral reefs. Savor a beachside lunch of grilled fish, soaking in the island’s rugged beauty.'),(406,82,5,'Tanah Lot & Canggu','Explore Tanah Lot Temple, photographing its iconic silhouette against the Indian Ocean’s waves. Relax in Canggu, surfing at Echo Beach or browsing bohemian boutiques. Savor a dinner of ayam betutu, embracing Canggu’s laid-back surf culture.'),(407,82,6,'Besakih Temple & Sidemen','Visit Besakih Temple, Bali’s “Mother Temple,” with its multi-tiered shrines nestled on Mount Agung’s slopes. Wander Sidemen’s rice fields, learning about traditional weaving and Balinese village life. Savor a lunch of nasi goreng, surrounded by Sidemen’s serene landscapes.'),(408,82,7,'Ubud Spa & Farewell','Indulge in a Balinese spa day in Ubud, enjoying a flower-petal massage and herbal steam bath. Shop at Ubud’s art market for batik textiles and wood carvings as souvenirs. Savor a farewell dinner of rijsttafel, toasting to Bali’s spiritual and natural splendor.'),(409,83,1,'Grand Palace & Wat Pho','Marvel at the Grand Palace’s glittering spires and emerald Buddha, a sacred icon shimmering in golden halls. Wander Wat Pho’s sprawling courtyards, gazing at the massive Reclining Buddha and intricate mosaic stupas. Savor a lunch of spicy som tam at a riverside eatery, with boats gliding along the Chao Phraya.'),(410,83,2,'Wat Arun & River Cruise','Climb Wat Arun’s steep steps, admiring its porcelain-encrusted towers glowing against the sunset over the river. Embark on a Chao Phraya River cruise, passing illuminated temples and bustling markets. Savor a dinner of pad Thai, watching the city’s skyline twinkle from the boat’s deck.'),(411,83,3,'Chatuchak Market & Jim Thompson','Explore Chatuchak Weekend Market’s labyrinthine stalls, bargaining for silk scarves, mango sticky rice, and carved Buddhas. Visit the Jim Thompson House, wandering its teak villas filled with Thai art and lush gardens. Savor a farewell lunch of khao soi, reflecting on Bangkok’s vibrant chaos.'),(412,84,1,'Grand Palace & Emerald Buddha','Tour the Grand Palace, awestruck by its golden chedis and the sacred Emerald Buddha in Wat Phra Kaew’s ornate chapel. Stroll the palace grounds, admiring murals depicting the Ramayana epic in vivid colors. Savor a lunch of green curry, immersed in Bangkok’s royal heritage.'),(413,84,2,'Ayutthaya Ancient Ruins','Journey to Ayutthaya, cycling through its UNESCO-listed ruins like Wat Mahathat, where Buddha heads entwined in tree roots captivate. Explore Wat Phra Si Sanphet’s towering chedis, glowing in the morning light. Savor a lunch of river prawns, reflecting on Thailand’s ancient capital.'),(414,84,3,'Damnoen Saduak Floating Market','Cruise Damnoen Saduak’s vibrant floating market, haggling for tropical fruits and coconut pancakes from canoe vendors. Paddle through narrow khlongs, passing stilted houses and fragrant spice stalls. Savor a dinner of tom yum goong, enjoying the market’s lively riverside ambiance.'),(415,84,4,'Wat Arun & Chinatown','Ascend Wat Arun’s prang, capturing views of Bangkok’s skyline and the river’s bustling ferries. Wander Chinatown’s Yaowarat Road, sampling street foods like mango sticky rice and crispy duck. Savor a late-night dessert of coconut ice cream, surrounded by neon signs and food carts.'),(416,84,5,'Jim Thompson & Suan Pakkad','Visit the Jim Thompson House, exploring its silk-weaving legacy and antique-filled teak villas. Tour Suan Pakkad Palace, wandering its lacquered pavilions and lush gardens with lotus ponds. Savor a lunch of massaman curry, soaking in Bangkok’s cultural treasures.'),(417,84,6,'Erawan Shrine & Lumpini Park','Offer flowers at Erawan Shrine, watching traditional Thai dancers perform amidst incense and bustling crowds. Stroll Lumpini Park, paddleboating on its lake and spotting monitor lizards. Savor a dinner of grilled seabass, relaxing in the park’s urban oasis.'),(418,84,7,'Chatuchak & Farewell','Shop at Chatuchak Market, navigating its 15,000 stalls for handicrafts, vintage clothes, and spicy snacks. Relax at a nearby café, sipping Thai iced tea while reflecting on your journey. Savor a farewell dinner of larb gai, toasting to Bangkok’s endless energy.'),(419,85,1,'Doi Suthep & Wat Umong','Ascend to Wat Phra That Doi Suthep, marveling at its golden chedi and panoramic views of Chiang Mai’s valley. Explore Wat Umong’s forest tunnels, filled with ancient stupas and meditative silence. Savor a lunch of khao soi, soaking in the temple’s serene ambiance.'),(420,85,2,'Night Bazaar & Old City','Wander Chiang Mai’s Night Bazaar, bargaining for silver jewelry, lanterns, and spicy sai ua sausages. Stroll the Old City’s moat, visiting Wat Chedi Luang’s towering ruins under starlit skies. Savor a dinner of gaeng hang lay, surrounded by the bazaar’s vibrant stalls.'),(421,85,3,'Warorot Market & Tha Pae','Explore Warorot Market, sampling dried mangoes and browsing colorful textiles in Chiang Mai’s bustling heart. Walk to Tha Pae Gate, joining locals for street food like grilled squid and papaya salad. Savor a farewell lunch of nam prik ong, celebrating the city’s northern charm.'),(422,86,1,'Doi Suthep & Bhubing Palace','Visit Wat Phra That Doi Suthep, ringing ceremonial bells and admiring its golden spire against misty mountains. Tour Bhubing Palace’s rose gardens, a royal retreat with fragrant blooms. Savor a lunch of khanom jeen, immersed in Chiang Mai’s spiritual heights.'),(423,86,2,'Elephant Sanctuary','Spend a day at an ethical elephant sanctuary, feeding and bathing gentle giants in a lush jungle setting. Learn about elephant conservation while walking alongside them through bamboo groves. Savor a vegetarian lunch of som tam, surrounded by the sanctuary’s peaceful riverside.'),(424,86,3,'Doi Inthanon National Park','Trek Doi Inthanon, Thailand’s highest peak, marveling at twin pagodas and misty waterfalls like Wachirathan. Visit Karen hill tribe villages, learning about their weaving and coffee farming traditions. Savor a lunch of wild mushroom curry, enjoying the park’s cool alpine air.'),(425,86,4,'Chiang Dao Caves & Hot Springs','Explore Chiang Dao Caves, wandering through limestone chambers filled with Buddha statues and stalactites. Relax at nearby hot springs, soaking in mineral-rich pools amidst tropical greenery. Savor a dinner of sticky rice and grilled fish, reflecting on the region’s natural wonders.'),(426,86,5,'Old City Temples','Tour Wat Phra Singh, admiring its golden lion statues and intricate Lanna murals in the Old City. Visit Wat Chiang Man, Chiang Mai’s oldest temple, with its ancient chedi guarded by stone elephants. Savor a lunch of gaeng phed ped yang, soaking in the city’s historic charm.'),(427,86,6,'Night Bazaar & Cooking Class','Shop at the Night Bazaar, haggling for carved soap flowers and handwoven scarves under colorful lights. Join a Thai cooking class, preparing dishes like green papaya salad and panang curry. Savor your creations at a communal dinner, celebrating Chiang Mai’s culinary heritage.'),(428,86,7,'Warorot & Farewell','Browse Warorot Market, tasting local snacks like miang kham and buying Lanna handicrafts. Relax at a riverside café, sipping Chiang Mai coffee while watching the Ping River flow. Savor a farewell dinner of khao niao mamuang, toasting to northern Thailand’s serene beauty.'),(429,87,1,'Patong Beach & Nightlife','Lounge on Patong Beach, swimming in turquoise waters and trying jet-skiing under the tropical sun. Explore Bangla Road’s vibrant nightlife, with neon-lit bars and live music echoing through the streets. Savor a dinner of Phuket lobster, enjoying the beach’s lively energy.'),(430,87,2,'Phi Phi Islands Day Trip','Sail to the Phi Phi Islands, snorkeling at Maya Bay’s emerald lagoon surrounded by limestone cliffs. Relax on Bamboo Island’s white sands, sipping fresh coconut water under swaying palms. Savor a seafood lunch on the boat, with waves lapping against the hull.'),(431,87,3,'Big Buddha & Chalong Temple','Visit Phuket’s Big Buddha, a 45-meter statue offering panoramic views of the Andaman Sea and lush hills. Tour Wat Chalong, admiring its golden pagoda and vibrant murals of Buddhist tales. Savor a lunch of moo hong, reflecting on Phuket’s spiritual serenity.'),(432,87,4,'Phuket Old Town','Wander Phuket Old Town’s Sino-Portuguese streets, photographing pastel shophouses and quirky street art. Browse Thalang Road’s markets for batik fabrics and spicy cashew snacks. Savor a farewell dinner of gaeng som, celebrating Phuket’s cultural charm.'),(433,88,1,'Patong & Freedom Beach','Relax on Patong Beach, kayaking along its crescent shore or lounging under colorful umbrellas. Hike to Freedom Beach, a secluded cove with powdery sand and crystal waters. Savor a lunch of tom kha gai, soaking in Phuket’s coastal paradise.'),(434,88,2,'Phi Phi & Maya Bay','Cruise to Phi Phi Islands, swimming in Maya Bay’s turquoise lagoon framed by dramatic cliffs. Snorkel at Pileh Lagoon, spotting clownfish and sea anemones in vibrant reefs. Savor a beachside dinner of grilled prawns, with stars reflecting on the Andaman Sea.'),(435,88,3,'Similan Islands Snorkeling','Sail to the Similan Islands, diving into pristine waters to explore coral gardens teeming with manta rays. Relax on Donald Duck Bay’s white sands, surrounded by granite boulders and jungle trails. Savor a picnic lunch of mango salad, immersed in the islands’ untouched beauty.'),(436,88,4,'James Bond Island','Visit Phang Nga Bay’s James Bond Island, marveling at its limestone pinnacle rising from emerald waters. Kayak through mangrove caves, discovering hidden lagoons and stalactite-filled grottoes. Savor a lunch of khao yam, enjoying the bay’s surreal limestone landscape.'),(437,88,5,'Phuket Old Town & Cooking','Stroll Phuket Old Town, visiting the Sunday Walking Street Market for pineapple fritters and handcrafted jewelry. Join a Thai cooking class, mastering dishes like massaman curry and mango sticky rice. Savor your creations at a communal lunch, celebrating Phuket’s culinary heritage.'),(438,88,6,'Big Buddha & Kata Beach','Tour the Big Buddha, capturing photos of its serene marble form against Phuket’s rolling hills. Relax on Kata Beach, surfing gentle waves or sipping cocktails at a beachfront bar. Savor a dinner of pla rad prik, enjoying the beach’s laid-back vibe.'),(439,88,7,'Promthep Cape & Farewell','Watch the sunset at Promthep Cape, Phuket’s southernmost point, with panoramic views of the Andaman Sea. Explore nearby Nai Harn Beach, swimming in its calm, turquoise lagoon. Savor a farewell dinner of Phuket-style crab curry, toasting to the island’s tropical allure.'),(440,89,1,'Shibuya & Harajuku','Cross Shibuya’s iconic scramble crossing, surrounded by neon billboards and bustling crowds. Wander Harajuku’s Takeshita Street, sampling crepes and browsing kawaii fashion shops. Savor a lunch of tonkotsu ramen, soaking in Tokyo’s vibrant youth culture.'),(441,89,2,'Senso-ji & Asakusa','Visit Senso-ji Temple, passing through the Kaminarimon Gate to admire its ancient pagoda and incense-filled courtyard. Stroll Nakamise Street, tasting ningyo-yaki cakes and buying paper fans. Savor a dinner of yakitori, enjoying Asakusa’s historic charm.'),(442,89,3,'Tsukiji & Ginza','Explore Tsukiji Outer Market, sampling fresh sushi and tamagoyaki from bustling stalls. Wander Ginza’s luxury boulevards, browsing flagship stores and modern art galleries. Savor a farewell lunch of katsu curry, celebrating Tokyo’s culinary and cosmopolitan flair.'),(443,90,1,'Shibuya & Meiji Shrine','Navigate Shibuya Crossing, capturing photos of its chaotic energy and towering LED screens. Visit Meiji Shrine, strolling through its forested paths to a serene torii gate and sacred sanctuary. Savor a lunch of okonomiyaki, immersed in Tokyo’s spiritual and modern contrast.'),(444,90,2,'Hakone Day Trip','Journey to Hakone, cruising Lake Ashi for views of Mount Fuji’s snow-capped peak on clear days. Explore the Open-Air Museum’s Picasso sculptures and volcanic Owakudani Valley’s sulfurous springs. Savor a dinner of shabu-shabu, reflecting on Hakone’s natural beauty.'),(445,90,3,'Senso-ji & Sky Tree','Tour Senso-ji, praying at its main hall and browsing Nakamise’s traditional crafts. Ascend Tokyo Sky Tree, marveling at 360-degree city views from its 450-meter observation deck. Savor a lunch of tempura soba, enjoying Asakusa’s blend of old and new.'),(446,90,4,'Akihabara & Ueno','Explore Akihabara’s neon-lit streets, shopping for anime merch and retro video games in multi-story arcades. Wander Ueno Park, visiting the Tokyo National Museum’s samurai armor and cherry blossom paths. Savor a dinner of gyudon, soaking in Tokyo’s otaku culture.'),(447,90,5,'Tsukiji & Odaiba','Sample sashimi at Tsukiji Outer Market, watching chefs slice tuna with precision. Visit Odaiba’s Rainbow Bridge, teamLab Borderless digital art museum, and futuristic DiverCity Gundam statue. Savor a lunch of chirashi, embracing Tokyo’s innovative spirit.'),(448,90,6,'Shinjuku & Kabukicho','Stroll Shinjuku’s Golden Gai, sipping sake in tiny bars tucked into narrow alleys. Visit the Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building for free panoramic city views at dusk. Savor a dinner of wagyu sukiyaki, immersed in Shinjuku’s electric nightlife.'),(449,90,7,'Ginza & Farewell','Shop in Ginza’s luxury boutiques, from Chanel to traditional wagashi confectioneries. Relax at Hama-rikyu Gardens, sipping matcha by a tidal pond with skyscrapers in the distance. Savor a farewell dinner of kaiseki, toasting to Tokyo’s endless wonders.'),(450,91,1,'Osaka Castle & Park','Tour Osaka Castle, climbing its keep for views of the city and its moat lined with cherry blossoms. Stroll the castle park, relaxing under plum trees and watching street musicians. Savor a lunch of kushikatsu, enjoying Osaka’s historic ambiance.'),(451,91,2,'Dotonbori & Shinsaibashi','Wander Dotonbori’s canal, sampling takoyaki and snapping photos of the iconic Glico Man sign. Explore Shinsaibashi’s shopping arcade, browsing for streetwear and matcha desserts. Savor a dinner of okonomiyaki, soaking in Osaka’s lively food scene.'),(452,91,3,'Umeda Sky & Amerikamura','Visit Umeda Sky Building’s Floating Garden, marveling at 360-degree views of Osaka’s skyline. Wander Amerikamura’s trendy streets, checking out vintage shops and street art murals. Savor a farewell lunch of kitsune udon, celebrating Osaka’s urban vibrancy.'),(453,92,1,'Osaka Castle & Sumiyoshi','Explore Osaka Castle, admiring its golden tiger ornaments and samurai history exhibits. Visit Sumiyoshi Taisha, crossing its red arched bridge to pray at one of Japan’s oldest shrines. Savor a lunch of battera sushi, immersed in Osaka’s historic roots.'),(454,92,2,'Kyoto’s Fushimi Inari','Journey to Kyoto, hiking Fushimi Inari’s vermilion torii gates winding up Mount Inari’s forested trails. Visit the shrine’s fox statues, leaving prayers for prosperity at hidden altars. Savor a dinner of yudofu, reflecting on Kyoto’s spiritual serenity.'),(455,92,3,'Kyoto’s Golden Pavilion','Tour Kinkaku-ji, Kyoto’s Golden Pavilion, shimmering in a pond framed by manicured pines and maples. Stroll the Ryoan-ji Zen rock garden, contemplating its minimalist beauty. Savor a lunch of kaiseki bento, surrounded by Kyoto’s temple elegance.'),(456,92,4,'Nara’s Deer Park','Visit Nara’s Todai-ji, marveling at the Great Buddha in the world’s largest wooden building. Feed friendly deer in Nara Park, wandering among ancient stone lanterns. Savor a lunch of kakinoha sushi, enjoying Nara’s tranquil heritage.'),(457,92,5,'Koya-san Spiritual Retreat','Travel to Koya-san, exploring Okunoin Cemetery’s mossy paths lined with 200,000 stone pagodas. Stay at a shukubo temple, joining monks for morning prayers and vegetarian shojin ryori. Savor a dinner of sesame tofu, immersed in Koya-san’s sacred silence.'),(458,92,6,'Dotonbori & Kuromon Market','Return to Osaka, strolling Dotonbori’s canal and tasting kobe beef skewers from street vendors. Shop at Kuromon Market, sampling grilled scallops and fresh persimmons. Savor a dinner of teppanyaki, celebrating Osaka’s culinary fame.'),(459,92,7,'Umeda & Farewell','Ascend Umeda Sky Building, capturing Osaka’s skyline from its open-air observatory. Wander Namba’s arcades, shopping for souvenirs like tenugui cloths and manju sweets. Savor a farewell dinner of negiyaki, toasting to Kansai’s cultural richness.'),(460,93,1,'Burj Khalifa & Dubai Mall','Ascend Burj Khalifa’s 124th floor, marveling at Dubai’s sprawling desert and glittering skyline below. Explore Dubai Mall, shopping at luxury boutiques and watching the aquarium’s sharks swim. Savor a lunch of lamb mandi, enjoying the mall’s opulent ambiance.'),(461,93,2,'Desert Safari & BBQ','Embark on a desert safari, dune-bashing in a 4x4 across golden 