waterfront.'),(468,94,6,'Old Dubai & Farewell','Explore Al Fahidi’s wind-towered houses, visiting the Dubai Museum in a 18th-century fort. Cruise Dubai Creek on an abra, shopping for gold and spices in Deira’s souks. Savor a farewell dinner of machboos, toasting to Dubai’s blend of heritage and innovation.'),(469,95,1,'Sheikh Zayed Mosque','Tour Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque, marveling at its white marble domes and world’s largest hand-knotted carpet. Wander its vast courtyard, reflecting in pools under golden chandeliers. Savor a lunch of shish taouk, soaking in the mosque’s serene grandeur.'),(470,95,2,'Louvre Abu Dhabi','Explore Louvre Abu Dhabi, admiring masterpieces from ancient Egypt to Monet under its iconic silver dome. Stroll the museum’s waterfront promenade, with Saadiyat Island’s mangroves in view. Savor a dinner of fattoush salad, reflecting on Abu Dhabi’s cultural ambition.'),(471,95,3,'Corniche & Heritage Village','Cycle along Abu Dhabi’s Corniche, enjoying sea breezes and views of the turquoise Persian Gulf. Visit the Heritage Village, exploring a reconstructed Bedouin camp with weaving and pottery demos. Savor a farewell lunch of harees, celebrating Abu Dhabi’s coastal charm.'),(472,96,1,'Sheikh Zayed & Qasr Al Hosn','Visit Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque, awestruck by its 82 domes and Swarovski crystal chandeliers. Tour Qasr Al Hosn, Abu Dhabi’s oldest fort, with exhibits on Emirati history. Savor a lunch of lamb saloona, immersed in the city’s spiritual and historic heart.'),(473,96,2,'Louvre & Saadiyat Island','Wander Louvre Abu Dhabi, discovering artifacts like Da Vinci’s works beneath a star-like dome. Relax on Saadiyat Beach, spotting dolphins in the Gulf’s turquoise waters. Savor a dinner of grilled hammour, enjoying the island’s artistic serenity.'),(474,96,3,'Yas Island Adventure','Thrill at Yas Island’s Ferrari World, riding Formula Rossa, the world’s fastest roller coaster. Explore Yas Marina Circuit, touring its Formula 1 track and luxury yachts. Savor a lunch of chicken shawarma, energized by Yas’s high-octane vibe.'),(475,96,4,'Liwa Oasis Desert','Journey to Liwa Oasis, dune-bashing across the Rub’ al Khali’s towering sands in a 4x4. Visit a date farm, tasting sweet varieties and learning about desert agriculture. Savor a Bedouin-style dinner of mansaf, camping under the desert’s starry expanse.'),(476,96,5,'Qasr Al Watan & Emirates Palace','Tour Qasr Al Watan, the presidential palace, marveling at its golden mosaics and vast library. Stroll Emirates Palace’s opulent grounds, sipping Arabic coffee in its gilded café. Savor a dinner of kabsa, reflecting on Abu Dhabi’s regal splendor.'),(477,96,6,'Corniche & Farewell','Walk the Corniche, enjoying its manicured gardens and views of Lulu Island’s mangroves. Shop at Marina Mall, bargaining for perfumes and Emirati sweets. Savor a farewell dinner of luqaimat with date syrup, toasting to Abu Dhabi’s cultural richness.'),(478,97,1,'Marina Bay & Skyline','Explore Marina Bay Sands, ascending its SkyPark for panoramic views of Singapore’s futuristic skyline. Wander the Helix Bridge, glowing with LED lights against the city’s towers. Savor a lunch of Hainanese chicken rice, soaking in Marina Bay’s modern marvels.'),(479,97,2,'Gardens by the Bay','Stroll Gardens by the Bay, marveling at Supertree Grove’s towering structures and Flower Dome’s exotic blooms. Walk the OCBC Skyway, swaying among the treetops with city views. Savor a dinner of chili crab, enjoying the gardens’ illuminated beauty.'),(480,97,3,'Chinatown & Little India','Wander Chinatown’s heritage streets, visiting Buddha Tooth Relic Temple and sampling dim sum. Explore Little India’s colorful Serangoon Road, buying jasmine garlands and tasting dosas. Savor a farewell lunch of laksa, celebrating Singapore’s cultural mosaic.'),(481,98,1,'Marina Bay & Merlion','Tour Marina Bay, photographing the Merlion statue spouting water against Singapore’s glittering skyline. Ascend Marina Bay Sands’ observation deck, capturing the city from 57 stories high. Savor a lunch of bak kut teh, immersed in Singapore’s iconic waterfront.'),(482,98,2,'Sentosa Island Adventure','Visit Sentosa Island, riding cable cars to Universal Studios for thrilling rides and Jurassic Park attractions. Relax on Palawan Beach, crossing its suspension bridge to a tiny islet. Savor a dinner of satay, enjoying Sentosa’s resort-like vibe.'),(483,98,3,'Gardens by the Bay & Clarke Quay','Explore Gardens by the Bay’s Cloud Forest, wandering misty trails with waterfalls and rare orchids. Stroll Clarke Quay’s riverside, dining at vibrant restaurants with live music. Savor a dinner of black pepper crab, soaking in the quay’s lively ambiance.'),(484,98,4,'Haw Par Villa & Cultural Park','Tour Haw Par Villa, marveling at its surreal statues depicting Chinese folklore and Ten Courts of Hell. Visit the Chinese and Japanese Gardens, strolling pagoda bridges and koi ponds. Savor a lunch of char kway teow, reflecting on Singapore’s cultural heritage.'),(485,98,5,'Pulau Ubin Island','Cycle Pulau Ubin’s rustic trails, exploring mangroves and spotting hornbills in a time-capsule village. Visit Chek Jawa Wetlands, walking boardwalks over seagrass lagoons and coral rubble. Savor a seafood lunch of fried prawns, enjoying the island’s serene escape.'),(486,98,6,'Orchard Road & Farewell','Shop on Orchard Road, browsing luxury malls and street markets for electronics and batik prints. Relax at Fort Canning Park, exploring its colonial bunkers and spice garden. Savor a farewell dinner of roti prata with curry, toasting to Singapore’s vibrant spirit.'),(487,99,1,'Hulhumale Beach & Snorkeling','Relax on Hulhumale Beach, swimming in turquoise waters and snorkeling among vibrant coral reefs. Stroll the beachfront promenade, sipping coconut water from roadside stalls. Savor a lunch of mas huni, enjoying the Maldives’ laid-back island vibe.'),(488,99,2,'Sultan Park & National Museum','Visit Sultan Park, wandering its lush gardens and the historic former palace grounds. Explore the National Museum, admiring coral stone carvings and ancient Quranic manuscripts. Savor a dinner of garudhiya, soaking in Male’s cultural heritage.'),(489,99,3,'Fish Market & Old Friday Mosque','Tour Male’s Fish Market, watching fishermen unload tuna and reef fish in a bustling waterfront scene. Visit the Old Friday Mosque, marveling at its coral stone walls and intricate woodcarvings. Savor a lunch of rihaakuru curry, immersed in the city’s maritime traditions.'),(490,99,4,'Sunset Cruise & Farewell','Embark on a sunset cruise, sailing past Male’s skyline and spotting dolphins in the Indian Ocean. Relax on deck, sipping tropical mocktails as the sky blazes orange. Savor a farewell dinner of grilled lobster, celebrating the Maldives’ tropical paradise.'),(491,100,1,'Hulhumale & Male City','Lounge on Hulhumale Beach, diving into crystal waters to snorkel among parrotfish and sea turtles. Wander Male’s Republic Square, photographing its flag-lined waterfront and bustling cafés. Savor a lunch of fihunu mas, soaking in the Maldives’ vibrant capital.'),(492,100,2,'South Male Atoll Snorkeling','Sail to South Male Atoll, snorkeling at Gulhi’s coral gardens filled with angelfish and moray eels. Relax on a sandbank, lounging under palms with turquoise waves lapping nearby. Savor a picnic lunch of tuna curry, immersed in the atoll’s pristine beauty.'),(493,100,3,'Maafushi Island','Visit Maafushi, swimming at Bikini Beach and trying kitesurfing in warm lagoon waters. Explore the island’s village, shopping for shell necklaces and tasting hedika snacks. Savor a dinner of grilled reef fish, enjoying Maafushi’s local charm.'),(494,100,4,'Banana Reef Diving','Dive at Banana Reef, exploring its coral caves and vibrant marine life like clownfish and manta rays. Surface to relax on a nearby islet, sipping fresh coconut water under the sun. Savor a lunch of mas riha, reflecting on the Maldives’ underwater wonders.'),(495,100,5,'Sandbank Picnic & Kayaking','Kayak to a secluded sandbank, picnicking on tropical fruits and Maldivian short eats amidst turquoise waters. Snorkel around the sandbank, spotting stingrays gliding over white sands. Savor a barbecue dinner of grilled prawns, surrounded by the ocean’s tranquility.'),(496,100,6,'Male Markets & Mosques','Shop at Male’s Local Market, bargaining for dried tuna and coconut sweets in a colorful maze. Visit the Grand Friday Mosque, admiring its golden dome and minimalist coral interiors. Savor a dinner of kandu kukulhu, celebrating Male’s cultural vibrancy.'),(497,100,7,'Dolphin Cruise & Farewell','Cruise the Indian Ocean, watching spinner dolphins leap against a fiery sunset. Relax on a dhoni boat, sipping passionfruit juice as stars emerge overhead. Savor a farewell dinner of lobster thermidor, toasting to the Maldives’ island magic.'),(498,101,1,'Avenida Paulista & MASP','Stroll Avenida Paulista, Sao Paulo’s bustling artery, lined with skyscrapers and street performers. Visit MASP, admiring its glass-suspended galleries with works by Botticelli and Portinari. Savor a lunch of feijoada, soaking in the city’s cosmopolitan energy.'),(499,101,2,'Ibirapuera Park & Museums','Relax in Ibirapuera Park, cycling past fountains and the Oca pavilion’s futuristic dome. Tour the Afro Brazil Museum, exploring vibrant exhibits on African diaspora culture. Savor a dinner of picanha, enjoying the park’s green oasis.'),(500,101,3,'Pinacoteca & Luz','Explore Pinacoteca do Estado, marveling at Brazilian art from colonial landscapes to modernist sculptures. Wander Luz Station’s Victorian architecture, sipping coffee at a nearby café. Savor a farewell lunch of pastel de queijo, celebrating Sao Paulo’s cultural depth.'),(501,102,1,'Avenida Paulista & Japan House','Walk Avenida Paulista, browsing bookstores and street art along its vibrant sidewalks. Visit Japan House, exploring minimalist exhibits on Japanese culture and design. Savor a lunch of moqueca, immersed in Sao Paulo’s global influences.'),(502,102,2,'Ibirapuera & MAM','Jog through Ibirapuera Park, admiring Niemeyer’s curved Marquise and serene lakes. Tour the Museum of Modern Art, viewing works by Tarsila do Amaral and Di Cavalcanti. Savor a dinner of coxinhas, relaxing in the park’s artistic ambiance.'),(503,102,3,'Embu das Artes Day Trip','Visit Embu das Artes, wandering its cobblestone streets filled with artisan shops and colonial churches. Browse the weekend art fair, buying hand-painted ceramics and wooden sculptures. Savor a lunch of barreado, enjoying Embu’s bohemian charm.'),(504,102,4,'Campos do Jordão','Journey to Campos do Jordão, exploring its Swiss-style chalets and misty pine forests in Brazil’s highlands. Ride the cable car to Morro do Elefante, capturing views of rolling hills. Savor a dinner of fondue, warmed by the town’s alpine coziness.'),(505,102,5,'Pinacoteca & Mercado Municipal','Tour Pinacoteca, admiring its red-brick galleries and Brazilian masterpieces like Almeida Júnior’s works. Shop at Mercado Municipal, tasting mortadella sandwiches and tropical fruits. Savor a lunch of tacacá, celebrating Sao Paulo’s culinary diversity.'),(506,102,6,'Vila Madalena & Farewell','Explore Vila Madalena’s colorful streets, photographing murals in Beco do Batman’s open-air gallery. Relax at a rooftop bar, sipping caipirinhas with city views. Savor a farewell dinner of virado à paulista, toasting to Sao Paulo’s vibrant spirit.'),(507,103,1,'Christ the Redeemer & Corcovado','Ascend Corcovado to Christ the Redeemer, marveling at Rio’s beaches and mountains from its outstretched arms. Hike trails around the statue, spotting toucans in Tijuca Forest. Savor a lunch of acarajé, soaking in Rio’s iconic skyline.'),(508,103,2,'Copacabana & Ipanema','Lounge on Copacabana Beach, playing beach volleyball and sipping água de coco under the sun. Stroll Ipanema’s shoreline, browsing beachfront kiosks and watching surfers. Savor a dinner of churrasco, enjoying Rio’s lively beach culture.'),(509,103,3,'Sugarloaf & Santa Teresa','Ride the cable car to Sugarloaf Mountain, capturing sunset views of Guanabara Bay and twinkling city lights. Wander Santa Teresa’s cobblestone streets, visiting art studios and colonial mansions. Savor a farewell lunch of bobó de camarão, celebrating Rio’s carioca charm.'),(510,104,1,'Christ the Redeemer & Tijuca','Visit Christ the Redeemer, photographing Rio’s sprawling beauty from Corcovado’s peak. Explore Tijuca National Park, hiking to waterfalls like Cascatinha Taunay amidst lush rainforest. Savor a lunch of feijoada, immersed in Rio’s natural splendor.'),(511,104,2,'Copacabana & Arpoador','Relax on Copacabana Beach, joining a beach soccer game or sipping caipirinhas by the waves. Watch sunset at Arpoador Rock, a surfer’s haven with panoramic ocean views. Savor a dinner of moqueca de peixe, enjoying Copacabana’s vibrant energy.'),(512,104,3,'Ilha Grande Day Trip','Sail to Ilha Grande, hiking to Lopes Mendes Beach’s powdery sands and turquoise waters. Snorkel in Lagoa Azul, spotting starfish and sergeant majors in crystal shallows. Savor a seafood lunch of grilled fish, surrounded by the island’s pristine beauty.'),(513,104,4,'Sugarloaf & Botafogo','Ascend Sugarloaf Mountain, riding cable cars for breathtaking views of Rio’s coastline and islands. Stroll Botafogo’s promenade, browsing indie bookstores and cozy cafés. Savor a dinner of pão de queijo and steak, soaking in Rio’s laid-back vibe.'),(514,104,5,'Santa Teresa & Lapa','Wander Santa Teresa’s bohemian streets, visiting the Selarón Steps’ colorful mosaics. Dance samba in Lapa’s Carioca Aqueduct district, with live music spilling from bars. Savor a lunch of escondidinho, celebrating Rio’s artistic heart.'),(515,104,6,'Sambadrome & Maracanã','Tour the Sambadrome, imagining Rio’s Carnival parades in its vibrant arena. Visit Maracanã Stadium, exploring its soccer history with trophies and Pelé’s legacy. Savor a dinner of frango com quiabo, reflecting on Rio’s cultural icons.'),(516,104,7,'Prainha & Farewell','Relax at Prainha Beach, a secluded surf spot framed by cliffs and Atlantic rainforest. Hike nearby trails, spotting marmosets and bromeliads in the wild. Savor a farewell dinner of camarão na moranga, toasting to Rio’s carioca spirit.'),(517,105,1,'Plaza de Mayo & Casa Rosada','Wander Plaza de Mayo, admiring the pink Casa Rosada and its balcony where Evita once spoke. Visit the Metropolitan Cathedral, marveling at its neoclassical facade and San Martín’s tomb. Savor a lunch of empanadas, soaking in Buenos Aires’ historic heart.'),(518,105,2,'San Telmo & Mercado','Explore San Telmo’s cobblestone streets, browsing antique shops and tango dancers in Plaza Dorrego. Shop at San Telmo Market, tasting choripán and dulce de leche pastries. Savor a dinner of asado, enjoying a live tango show’s passionate rhythms.'),(519,105,3,'La Boca & Caminito','Stroll La Boca’s Caminito, photographing its rainbow-colored tenements and street art murals. Visit La Bombonera stadium, feeling the passion of Boca Juniors’ soccer legacy. Savor a farewell lunch of milanesa, celebrating Buenos Aires’ vibrant culture.'),(520,106,1,'Plaza de Mayo & Cabildo','Tour Plaza de Mayo, exploring the Cabildo’s colonial museum and the Casa Rosada’s grand halls. Stroll Avenida de Mayo, admiring its Belle Époque architecture and cozy cafés. Savor a lunch of locro, immersed in Buenos Aires’ revolutionary roots.'),(521,106,2,'Recoleta & Cemetery','Visit Recoleta Cemetery, wandering marble mausoleums where Evita Perón rests in eternal elegance. Tour the National Museum of Fine Arts, admiring Argentine works by Berni and Quinquela Martín. Savor a dinner of bife de chorizo, soaking in Recoleta’s refined charm.'),(522,106,3,'Tigre Delta Day Trip','Cruise the Tigre Delta, navigating its labyrinthine rivers past stilted houses and lush islands. Visit Tigre’s Puerto de Frutos, shopping for wicker baskets and artisanal jams. Savor a lunch of pacú fish, enjoying the delta’s serene waterways.'),(523,106,4,'San Telmo & Tango Class','Wander San Telmo, browsing vintage records and tango memorabilia in its bohemian shops. Join a tango class, learning sultry steps with a milonga instructor. Savor a dinner of provoleta, swaying to live bandoneón music in a dimly lit salon.'),(524,106,5,'La Boca & Palermo','Explore La Boca’s colorful Caminito, watching street tango and buying vibrant paintings. Stroll Palermo’s trendy streets, sipping cortados at hip cafés and browsing boutiques. Savor a lunch of choripán, embracing Buenos Aires’ artistic diversity.'),(525,106,6,'Colonia del Sacramento','Ferry to Colonia del Sacramento, Uruguay, wandering its UNESCO-listed cobblestone streets and Portuguese fort. Climb the lighthouse for views of the Río de la Plata’s shimmering expanse. Savor a dinner of chivito, reflecting on the region’s colonial heritage.'),(526,106,7,'Palermo Soho & Farewell','Shop in Palermo Soho’s chic boutiques, finding leather goods and Argentine wines. Relax at Jardín Botánico, strolling among native flora and serene lagoons. Savor a farewell dinner of lomo al malbec, toasting to Buenos Aires’ passionate spirit.'),(527,107,1,'Plaza de Armas & Cathedral','Stroll Plaza de Armas, admiring Lima’s colonial cathedral and the ornate Government Palace. Tour the Monastery of San Francisco, exploring its catacombs and baroque library. Savor a lunch of ceviche, soaking in Lima’s historic grandeur.'),(528,107,2,'Larcomar & Miraflores','Visit Larcomar, a cliffside mall in Miraflores, shopping with views of the Pacific Ocean. Wander Parque del Amor, photographing its colorful mosaic walls and kissing statue. Savor a dinner of lomo saltado, enjoying Miraflores’ coastal charm.'),(529,107,3,'Huaca Pucllana & Barranco','Tour Huaca Pucllana, an ancient adobe pyramid glowing under Lima’s desert sun. Explore Barranco’s bohemian streets, visiting art galleries and the Bridge of Sighs. Savor a farewell lunch of causa limeña, celebrating Lima’s vibrant culture.'),(530,108,1,'Plaza de Armas & Larco Museum','Wander Plaza de Armas, photographing the Archbishop’s Palace and its carved balconies. Visit Museo Larco, marveling at pre-Columbian ceramics and golden Moche artifacts. Savor a lunch of anticuchos, immersed in Lima’s ancient and colonial layers.'),(531,108,2,'Pachacamac Ruins','Journey to Pachacamac, exploring its sprawling adobe temples dedicated to the oracle god. Wander the site’s pyramids, imagining Inca pilgrimages under the coastal sun. Savor a dinner of aji de gallina, reflecting on Peru’s pre-Hispanic heritage.'),(532,108,3,'Miraflores & Cooking Class','Stroll Miraflores’ Malecón, cycling along cliffs with Pacific waves crashing below. Join a Peruvian cooking class, preparing dishes like ceviche and pisco sours. Savor your creations at a communal lunch, celebrating Lima’s culinary fame.'),(533,108,4,'Paracas & Ballestas Islands','Travel to Paracas, cruising the Ballestas Islands to see sea lions and Humboldt penguins. Explore Paracas National Reserve’s red sand beaches and flamingo-filled lagoons. Savor a lunch of scallop ceviche, surrounded by the reserve’s stark beauty.'),(534,108,5,'Huacachina Oasis','Visit Huacachina, sandboarding down dunes surrounding a palm-fringed desert lagoon. Ride a dune buggy, racing across the Ica Desert’s golden sands at sunset. Savor a dinner of pollo a la brasa, relaxing by the oasis’ tranquil waters.'),(535,108,6,'Barranco & Art Scene','Wander Barranco’s colorful streets, visiting MATE Museum’s Mario Testino photography exhibits. Relax at a peña, enjoying live criolla music and pisco cocktails. Savor a lunch of arroz con pato, soaking in Barranco’s bohemian vibe.'),(536,108,7,'Callao & Farewell','Explore Callao’s Real Felipe Fortress, a colonial stronghold with cannons overlooking the Pacific. Stroll La Punta’s seaside promenade, tasting fresh fish tiradito. Savor a farewell dinner of rocoto relleno, toasting to Lima’s coastal splendor.'),(537,109,1,'Plaza de Armas & Mercado Central','Wander Plaza de Armas, admiring Santiago’s neoclassical cathedral and lively street performers. Shop at Mercado Central, tasting empanadas de pino and fresh ceviche. Savor a lunch of pastel de choclo, soaking in the city’s colonial heart.'),(538,109,2,'Cerro San Cristóbal & Bellavista','Ride the funicular to Cerro San Cristóbal, enjoying panoramic views of Santiago and the Andes. Stroll Bellavista’s colorful streets, visiting La Chascona, Pablo Neruda’s eclectic home. Savor a dinner of cazuela, immersed in the neighborhood’s bohemian charm.'),(539,109,3,'Santa Lucía & Lastarria','Climb Cerro Santa Lucía, exploring its terraced gardens and historic Hidalgo Castle. Wander Lastarria’s trendy streets, browsing bookstores and sipping Chilean wine at cafés. Savor a farewell lunch of porotos granados, celebrating Santiago’s urban vibrancy.'),(540,110,1,'Plaza de Armas & Museo Chileno','Tour Plaza de Armas, photographing the Metropolitan Cathedral’s ornate facade and bronze statues. Visit Museo Chileno de Arte Precolombino, admiring Mapuche textiles and Inca quipus. Savor a lunch of humitas, immersed in Santiago’s cultural core.'),(541,110,2,'Valparaíso Day Trip','Journey to Valparaíso, wandering its UNESCO-listed hills with vibrant street art and funiculars. Stroll Cerro Concepción, visiting cafés and colonial-era mansions overlooking the Pacific. Savor a dinner of chorrillana, enjoying Valpo’s bohemian seaside vibe.'),(542,110,3,'Maipo Valley Wine Tour','Explore Maipo Valley’s vineyards, tasting Carmenère and Cabernet Sauvignon at Concha y Toro. Tour a historic cellar, learning about Chile’s winemaking heritage amidst oak barrels. Savor a lunch of asado al palo, paired with wines in a vine-clad courtyard.'),(543,110,4,'Cerro San Cristóbal & Bellavista','Ascend Cerro San Cristóbal, cycling through Parque Metropolitano’s trails with Andean views. Tour La Chascona in Bellavista, exploring Neruda’s quirky nautical-themed home. Savor a dinner of curanto, reflecting on Santiago’s poetic charm.'),(544,110,5,'Portillo & Andes Trek','Visit Portillo, hiking in the Andes near Laguna del Inca’s turquoise waters and snow-capped peaks. Learn about Andean condors at a local conservation center. Savor a lunch of charquicán, warmed by the crisp mountain air.'),(545,110,6,'Cajón del Maipo','Explore Cajón del Maipo, rafting the Maipo River’s rapids or soaking in Termas Colina’s hot springs. Hike to El Morado Glacier, spotting guanacos amidst rugged peaks. Savor a dinner of empanadas de horno, surrounded by the canyon’s dramatic landscapes.'),(546,110,7,'Lastarria & Farewell','Wander Lastarria, shopping for lapis lazuli jewelry and tasting mote con huesillo at cafés. Relax at Parque Forestal, strolling along the Mapocho River’s tree-lined paths. Savor a farewell dinner of pebre-topped bistec a lo pobre, toasting to Chile’s Andean spirit.'),(547,111,1,'Sydney Opera House & The Rocks','Tour the Sydney Opera House, marveling at its sail-like shells and harborfront stage. Wander The Rocks’ cobblestone lanes, browsing markets and historic pubs. Savor a lunch of fish and chips, soaking in Sydney’s iconic waterfront.'),(548,111,2,'Bondi Beach & Coastal Walk','Relax on Bondi Beach, surfing waves or lounging with a flat white from a beachside café. Hike the Bondi to Coogee Coastal Walk, passing Tamarama’s turquoise coves. Savor a dinner of barramundi, enjoying Bondi’s laid-back vibe.'),(549,111,3,'Harbour Bridge & Circular Quay','Climb the Sydney Harbour Bridge, capturing panoramic views of the Opera House and skyline. Stroll Circular Quay, watching ferries and street performers by the water. Savor a farewell lunch of meat pies, celebrating Sydney’s harbor charm.'),(550,112,1,'Sydney Opera House & Botanic Garden','Explore the Sydney Opera House, joining a backstage tour of its theaters and green rooms. Stroll the Royal Botanic Garden, spotting ibis and Wollemi pines by the harbor. Savor a lunch of Moreton Bay bugs, immersed in Sydney’s waterfront splendor.'),(551,112,2,'Blue Mountains Day Trip','Journey to the Blue Mountains, hiking to Wentworth Falls and spotting lyrebirds in eucalyptus forests. Visit Scenic World, riding the Skyway cable car over Jamison Valley’s misty cliffs. Savor a dinner of kangaroo steak, reflecting on the region’s rugged beauty.'),(552,112,3,'Bondi & Bronte Beaches','Lounge on Bondi Beach, trying a surf lesson or sipping smoothies at Icebergs. Walk to Bronte Beach, relaxing in its rock pool with waves crashing nearby. Savor a lunch of prawn rolls, enjoying Sydney’s coastal lifestyle.'),(553,112,4,'Hunter Valley Wine Tour','Tour Hunter Valley’s vineyards, tasting Shiraz and Semillon at boutique wineries like Tyrrell’s. Explore the region’s olive groves and cheese farms, sampling local artisan products. Savor a lunch of wood-fired pizza, paired with wines in a vine-draped setting.'),(554,112,5,'Manly Beach & Ferry Ride','Ferry to Manly Beach, surfing its rolling waves or cycling the seaside promenade. Hike North Head, capturing views of Sydney’s skyline and Pacific cliffs. Savor a dinner of grilled octopus, soaking in Manly’s relaxed beach vibe.'),(555,112,6,'The Rocks & Harbour Cruise','Wander The Rocks, visiting the Museum of Contemporary Art and colonial-era pubs. Embark on a sunset harbor cruise, sailing past Luna Park and Fort Denison. Savor a dinner of lamb cutlets, enjoying the harbor’s twinkling lights.'),(556,112,7,'Taronga Zoo & Farewell','Visit Taronga Zoo, meeting koalas, kangaroos, and platypuses with harbor views. Relax at Mrs Macquarie’s Chair, photographing the Opera House at dusk. Savor a farewell dinner of pavlova, toasting to Sydney’s natural and urban allure.'),(557,113,1,'Federation Square & NGV','Explore Federation Square, admiring its geometric architecture and bustling cultural events. Visit the National Gallery of Victoria, marveling at Aboriginal art and global masterpieces. Savor a lunch of dim sims, soaking in Melbourne’s artistic heart.'),(558,113,2,'Queen Victoria Market & Laneways','Shop at Queen Victoria Market, tasting fresh oysters and artisanal cheeses in its historic sheds. Wander Melbourne’s street art laneways, photographing murals in Hosier Lane. Savor a dinner of gourmet burgers, enjoying the city’s creative vibe.'),(559,113,3,'Eureka Skydeck & Southbank','Ascend Eureka Skydeck, capturing 360-degree views of Melbourne’s skyline and Yarra River. Stroll Southbank’s promenade, browsing riverside cafés and public art. Savor a farewell lunch of lamingtons, celebrating Melbourne’s urban charm.'),(560,114,1,'Federation Square & Flinders Street','Wander Federation Square, joining a free art talk or sipping coffee at its open-air plaza. Photograph Flinders Street Station’s iconic clocks and Edwardian facade. Savor a lunch of Vietnamese pho, immersed in Melbourne’s cultural hub.'),(561,114,2,'Great Ocean Road & Twelve Apostles','Drive the Great Ocean Road, marveling at the Twelve Apostles’ limestone stacks rising from the Southern Ocean. Explore Loch Ard Gorge, hearing tales of shipwrecks amidst dramatic cliffs. Savor a dinner of fish tacos, surrounded by the coast’s wild beauty.'),(562,114,3,'Phillip Island Penguin Parade','Visit Phillip Island, watching little penguins waddle ashore at dusk in a natural amphitheater. Tour the Koala Conservation Centre, spotting marsupials in eucalyptus canopies. Savor a lunch of seafood chowder, enjoying the island’s wildlife wonders.'),(563,114,4,'Yarra Valley Wine Tour','Explore Yarra Valley’s vineyards, tasting Pinot Noir and Chardonnay at Domaine Chandon. Visit a dairy farm, sampling handcrafted cheeses and local honey. Savor a lunch of charcuterie, paired with wines in a rolling hillside setting.'),(564,114,5,'Mornington Peninsula','Tour Mornington Peninsula, relaxing at Peninsula Hot Springs’ geothermal pools amidst native bushland. Hike Cape Schanck, capturing views of Bass Strait’s rugged cliffs. Savor a dinner of roasted lamb, reflecting on the peninsula’s coastal serenity.'),(565,114,6,'Melbourne Laneways & St Kilda','Wander Melbourne’s laneways, sipping flat whites at Degraves Street’s hidden cafés. Relax at St Kilda Beach, watching kite surfers and the iconic Palais Theatre. Savor a lunch of souvlaki, enjoying St Kilda’s bohemian seaside vibe.'),(566,114,7,'Royal Botanic Gardens & Farewell','Stroll Melbourne’s Royal Botanic Gardens, exploring fern gullies and the Aboriginal Heritage Walk. Relax by the Ornamental Lake, sipping tea at the Terrace café. Savor a farewell dinner of barramundi, toasting to Victoria’s urban and natural splendor.'),(567,115,1,'Sky Tower & Viaduct Harbour','Ascend Sky Tower, marveling at 360-degree views of Auckland’s harbors and volcanic cones. Stroll Viaduct Harbour, watching yachts and dining at waterfront bistros. Savor a lunch of green-lipped mussels, soaking in Auckland’s nautical charm.'),(568,115,2,'Waiheke Island Day Trip','Ferry to Waiheke Island, touring vineyards like Mudbrick for Sauvignon Blanc tastings. Relax on Oneroa Beach, swimming in clear waters with rolling hills in view. Savor a dinner of lamb rack, enjoying Waiheke’s Mediterranean vibe.'),(569,115,3,'Auckland Domain & Museum','Explore Auckland Domain, wandering its fern-filled paths and historic Wintergardens. Visit the Auckland War Memorial Museum, admiring Māori taonga and Pacific artifacts. Savor a farewell lunch of hāngī, celebrating Auckland’s cultural richness.'),(570,116,1,'Sky Tower & Mt Eden','Ride to Sky Tower’s observation deck, capturing Auckland’s skyline and distant Hauraki Gulf islands. Hike Mount Eden’s volcanic crater, strolling its grassy rim for city views. Savor a lunch of fish and chips, immersed in Auckland’s urban and natural blend.'),(571,116,2,'Waiheke Island & Wineries','Sail to Waiheke Island, tasting Pinot Gris at Stonyridge Vineyard’s olive-shaded terraces. Cycle to Onetangi Beach, relaxing on golden sands with a chilled rosé. Savor a dinner of venison, enjoying Waiheke’s island tranquility.'),(572,116,3,'Rotorua Geothermal Wonders','Journey to Rotorua, exploring Wai-O-Tapu’s bubbling mud pools and Champagne Pool’s vibrant colors. Visit Te Puia, watching geysers erupt and Māori carvers craft kowhaiwhai patterns. Savor a lunch of Māori fry bread, surrounded by geothermal steam.'),(573,116,4,'Rotorua Māori Culture','Attend a Māori cultural show at Whakarewarewa, learning haka and poi dance amidst carved meeting houses. Relax in Polynesian Spa’s hot mineral pools, overlooking Lake Rotorua. Savor a dinner of hāngī, celebrating New Zealand’s indigenous heritage.'),(574,116,5,'Waitomo Glowworm Caves','Explore Waitomo Caves, drifting by boat under glowworms twinkling like a starry sky. Abseil into Ruakuri Cave, marveling at limestone formations and underground rivers. Savor a lunch of lamb sliders, reflecting on Waitomo’s subterranean magic.'),(575,116,6,'Coromandel Peninsula','Visit Coromandel, digging your own hot pool at Hot Water Beach’s geothermal sands. Hike to Cathedral Cove’s limestone arch, swimming in turquoise waters below. Savor a dinner of paua fritters, enjoying Coromandel’s coastal serenity.'),(576,116,7,'Auckland Museum & Farewell','Tour Auckland Museum, exploring Māori and Pacific galleries with taiaha weapons and waka canoes. Relax at Mission Bay, sipping coffee with harbor views. Savor a farewell dinner of kumara gnocchi, toasting to New Zealand’s North Island beauty.'),(577,117,1,'Fiji Museum & Thurston Gardens','Visit the Fiji Museum, admiring ancient Lapita pottery and a 13-meter war canoe. Stroll Thurston Gardens, spotting tropical orchids and banyan trees in Suva’s green heart. Savor a lunch of kokoda, soaking in the city’s colonial history.'),(578,117,2,'Colo-i-Suva Forest Park','Hike Colo-i-Suva Forest Park, swimming in waterfall pools and spotting parrots in mahogany forests. Picnic by Waisila Creek, listening to the jungle’s chorus of birds and rustling leaves. Savor a dinner of lovo, enjoying the park’s tranquil escape.'),(579,117,3,'Municipal Market & Suva Point','Shop at Suva’s Municipal Market, bargaining for kava roots, taro, and handwoven mats. Walk Suva Point’s waterfront, watching fishing boats bob in Laucala Bay. Savor a farewell lunch of rourou stew, celebrating Fiji’s vibrant culture.'),(580,118,1,'Fiji Museum & Suva City','Tour the Fiji Museum, marveling at cannibal forks and traditional masi cloth displays. Wander Suva’s Victoria Parade, browsing colonial buildings and local cafés. Savor a lunch of palusami, immersed in Suva’s multicultural heritage.'),(581,118,2,'Colo-i-Suva & Village Visit','Trek Colo-i-Suva Forest Park, diving into crystal pools beneath Upper Waimanu Falls. Visit a Fijian village, joining a kava ceremony and learning about lovo cooking. Savor a dinner of vakalolo, enjoying the forest’s lush serenity.'),(582,118,3,'Sigatoka Sand Dunes','Explore Sigatoka Sand Dunes National Park, hiking trails with views of Fiji’s coral coast and ancient pottery shards. Visit Sigatoka Market, tasting fresh pineapple and cassava chips. Savor a lunch of fish in lolo, reflecting on Fiji’s archaeological treasures.'),(583,118,4,'Sabeto Hot Springs & Mud Pools','Relax at Sabeto Hot Springs, soaking in warm mud pools and mineral-rich geothermal waters. Wander nearby orchid gardens, spotting vibrant blooms and tropical birds. Savor a dinner of ika vakalolo, surrounded by Sabeto’s lush valley.'),(584,118,5,'Coral Coast Snorkeling','Snorkel along Viti Levu’s Coral Coast, swimming among vibrant reefs and clownfish near Natadola Beach. Relax on the beach, sipping coconut water under swaying palms. Savor a lunch of chicken curry, enjoying the coast’s tropical paradise.'),(585,118,6,'Suva Markets & Farewell','Browse Suva’s Municipal Market, buying woven baskets and fresh soursop for souvenirs. Relax at My Suva Park, picnicking with views of the harbor’s anchored yachts. Savor a farewell dinner of kokoda ceviche, toasting to Fiji’s island spirit.'),(586,119,1,'Denarau Island & Port','Relax on Denarau Island’s beaches, paddleboarding in calm lagoon waters with resort views. Stroll Port Denarau, shopping for Fijian pearls and sipping mango smoothies. Savor a lunch of walu fish, enjoying Nadi’s luxurious coastal vibe.'),(587,119,2,'Garden of the Sleeping Giant','Wander the Garden of the Sleeping Giant, marveling at 2,000 orchid varieties and lily-covered ponds. Hike to Wailoaloa Beach, spotting herons along the shore. Savor a dinner of palusami, surrounded by the garden’s tropical serenity.'),(588,119,3,'Sri Siva Temple & Markets','Visit Sri Siva Subramaniya Temple, admiring its rainbow-colored Dravidian gopuram and carved deities. Shop at Nadi Market, tasting roti wraps and buying sulu fabrics. Savor a farewell lunch of lovo chicken, celebrating Nadi’s cultural diversity.'),(589,120,1,'Denarau & Sunset Cruise','Lounge on Denarau Island, kayaking its turquoise lagoons with palm-fringed shores. Embark on a sunset cruise, sipping cocktails as the sky glows over the Pacific. Savor a dinner of kokoda, enjoying Denarau’s resort-like ambiance.'),(590,120,2,'Yasawa Islands Day Trip','Sail to the Yasawa Islands, snorkeling at Sawa-i-Lau Caves’ limestone grottos filled with clear waters. Relax on Drawaqa Island’s beaches, spotting manta rays in nearby channels. Savor a beach barbecue of grilled fish, immersed in the Yasawas’ pristine beauty.'),(591,120,3,'Mamanuca Islands','Cruise to the Mamanuca Islands, swimming at Monuriki’s lagoon, famous from Cast Away. Snorkel Cloud 9’s floating platform, surrounded by coral reefs and tropical fish. Savor a lunch of lovo pork, enjoying the islands’ idyllic setting.'),(592,120,4,'Natadola Beach & Horseback','Gallop along Natadola Beach’s golden sands, with turquoise waves crashing and distant coral reefs shimmering. Stop for a swim in the warm Pacific, spotting tropical fish near the shore. Savor a beachside lunch of cassava fries, soaking in Fiji’s coastal paradise.'),(593,120,5,'Garden of the Sleeping Giant','Wander the Garden of the Sleeping Giant, marveling at vibrant orchids and serene lily ponds nestled in a lush valley. Hike to a lookout, capturing views of the Sabeto Mountains framed by tropical greenery. Savor a dinner of rourou soup, surrounded by the garden’s tranquil beauty.'),(594,120,6,'Sri Siva Temple & Mud Pools','Visit Sri Siva Subramaniya Temple, admiring its colorful Dravidian carvings and fragrant incense offerings. Relax at Sabeto Mud Pools, soaking in warm geothermal mud and mineral springs. Savor a lunch of chicken palau, reflecting on Nadi’s cultural and natural blend.'),(595,120,7,'Nadi Markets & Farewell','Shop at Nadi Market, bargaining for handwoven mats, kava bowls, and fresh pineapple slices. Relax at Wailoaloa Beach, watching the sunset paint the sky over the Pacific. Savor a farewell dinner of lovo feast, toasting to Fiji’s island allure.'),(596,121,1,'Waikiki Beach & Diamond Head','Lounge on Waikiki Beach, surfing gentle waves or sipping mai tais under swaying palms. Hike Diamond Head’s volcanic crater, capturing panoramic views of Honolulu’s coastline. Savor a lunch of loco moco, enjoying Waikiki’s vibrant beach vibe.'),(597,121,2,'Pearl Harbor & USS Arizona','Tour Pearl Harbor’s USS Arizona Memorial, reflecting on history amidst the sunken battleship’s rusted remains. Visit the Pacific Aviation Museum, exploring WWII planes in historic hangars. Savor a dinner of kalua pork, immersed in Oahu’s solemn heritage.'),(598,121,3,'Iolani Palace & Downtown','Explore Iolani Palace, wandering its royal chambers and koa wood staircase, a symbol of Hawaiian monarchy. Stroll downtown Honolulu, admiring the Kamehameha Statue and historic missionary houses. Savor a farewell lunch of poke bowls, celebrating Oahu’s cultural heart.'),(599,122,1,'Waikiki & Kapiolani Park','Relax on Waikiki Beach, paddleboarding in turquoise waters with Diamond Head looming nearby. Stroll Kapiolani Park, joining locals for ukulele jams under banyan trees. Savor a lunch of laulau, soaking in Honolulu’s laid-back coastal charm.'),(600,122,2,'Pearl Harbor & Battleship Missouri','Visit Pearl Harbor, touring the USS Arizona Memorial and the mighty Battleship Missouri’s decks. Explore the Bowfin Submarine Museum, crawling through tight hatches of a WWII sub. Savor a dinner of chicken katsu, reflecting on Oahu’s military history.'),(601,122,3,'Hanauma Bay Snorkeling','Snorkel Hanauma Bay’s coral reefs, swimming with green sea turtles and vibrant parrotfish in a volcanic crater. Relax on the beach, sipping passionfruit juice under coconut palms. Savor a lunch of shrimp tacos, enjoying the bay’s underwater paradise.'),(602,122,4,'North Shore & Surfing','Drive to Oahu’s North Shore, watching pro surfers ride massive waves at Banzai Pipeline. Visit Waimea Valley, hiking to a waterfall pool surrounded by botanical gardens. Savor a dinner of garlic shrimp, soaking in the North Shore’s surf culture.'),(603,122,5,'Polynesian Cultural Center','Tour the Polynesian Cultural Center, learning hula in a Hawaiian village and fire-knife dancing in Samoa. Paddle a canoe through a lagoon, passing Tongan drummers and Fijian warriors. Savor a luau dinner of poi and roasted pig, celebrating Polynesian traditions.'),(604,122,6,'Kailua & Lanikai Beaches','Kayak to Lanikai Beach, lounging on powdery sands with the Mokulua Islands in view. Hike Kailua’s Pillbox Trail, capturing turquoise ocean vistas from WWII bunkers. Savor a lunch of ahi poke, enjoying the windward coast’s serene beauty.'),(605,122,7,'Iolani Palace & Farewell','Visit Iolani Palace, exploring its throne room and royal artifacts of Hawaii’s last monarchs. Shop at Ala Moana Center, bargaining for leis and macadamia chocolates. Savor a farewell dinner of mahi-mahi, toasting to Oahu’s aloha spirit.'),(606,123,1,'Point Venus & Black Sand Beach','Visit Point Venus, strolling its black sand beach where Captain Cook once landed, with Tahiti’s mountains in view. Swim in the calm lagoon, spotting fish darting in clear waters. Savor a lunch of poisson cru, soaking in Papeete’s tropical allure.'),(607,123,2,'Papeete Market & Notre Dame','Wander Papeete Market, bargaining for vanilla pods, pareu fabrics, and fresh breadfruit. Tour Notre Dame Basilica, admiring its yellow facade and Polynesian wood carvings. Savor a dinner of fafa chicken, enjoying the market’s vibrant energy.'),(608,123,3,'Faarumai Waterfalls','Hike to Faarumai Waterfalls, marveling at three cascading falls surrounded by lush jungle and ferns. Picnic by Vaimahuta Falls, listening to the roar of water and tropical birds. Savor a lunch of tamure fish, immersed in Tahiti’s rainforest serenity.'),(609,123,4,'Tahiti Sunset & Farewell','Embark on a sunset lagoon cruise, sailing past Papeete’s skyline with Moorea’s peaks on the horizon. Relax on deck, sipping hibiscus punch as the sky glows pink. Savor a farewell dinner of coconut-crusted prawns, celebrating Tahiti’s island magic.'),(610,124,1,'Point Venus & Arahurahu Marae','Explore Point Venus, walking its historic lighthouse and black sand shores with lagoon views. Visit Arahurahu Marae, a restored Polynesian temple with stone altars and sacred legends. Savor a lunch of ma’a tinito, immersed in Tahiti’s ancient heritage.'),(611,124,2,'Papeete Market & Bougainville Park','Shop at Papeete Market, tasting monoi oil soaps and tropical fruit smoothies in a colorful maze. Stroll Bougainville Park, relaxing by fountains with frangipani scents in the air. Savor a dinner of poisson cru, enjoying Papeete’s lively Polynesian vibe.'),(612,124,3,'Moorea Day Trip','Ferry to Moorea, snorkeling in Opunohu Bay’s coral gardens with stingrays and blacktip sharks. Hike Belvedere Lookout, capturing views of Cook’s Bay and emerald valleys. Savor a lunch of grilled mahi-mahi, surrounded by Moorea’s dramatic peaks.'),(613,124,4,'Faarumai & Vaipahi Gardens','Trek to Faarumai Waterfalls, swimming in cool pools beneath jungle-clad cliffs. Wander Vaipahi Gardens, exploring trails with hibiscus blooms and sacred spring caves. Savor a dinner of chicken in vanilla sauce, reflecting on Tahiti’s natural splendor.'),(614,124,5,'Teahupo’o & Surfing','Visit Teahupo’o, watching world-class surfers tackle its legendary reef break waves. Relax on the black sand beach, sipping coconut water with the Pacific’s roar nearby. Savor a lunch of firi firi doughnuts, enjoying the village’s laid-back vibe.'),(615,124,6,'Arahoho Blowhole & Lagoonarium','Marvel at Arahoho Blowhole, where ocean waves erupt through volcanic rock with a thunderous spray. Snorkel at the Lagoonarium, swimming with tropical fish and feeding sharks in a coral lagoon. Savor a dinner of breadfruit curry, soaking in Tahiti’s coastal wonders.'),(616,124,7,'Tahiti Spa & Farewell','Indulge in a Polynesian spa day, enjoying a tamanu oil massage and tamarind scrub by the lagoon. Shop at Papeete’s Le Marché for pearl jewelry and carved tikis as souvenirs. Savor a farewell dinner of octopus in coconut milk, toasting to Tahiti’s tropical paradise.');
